145 // For TLS on AIX, we need to be able to identify TOC entries of specific ----

147 // entries. So each entry is represented by a pair of MCSymbol and ----
148 // VariantKind. For example, we need to be able to identify the following ----
149 // entry as a TLSGD entry so we can add the @m relocation: ----
150 // .tc .i[TC],i[TL]@m ----
151 // By default, VK_None is used for the VariantKind. ----
152 MapVector, ----
153 MCSymbol *> ----
154 TOC; ----

156 ----

299 void PPCAsmPrinter::PrintSymbolOperand(const MachineOperand &MO, 0
300 raw_ostream &O) { ----
301 // Computing the address of a global symbol, not calling it. ----
302 const GlobalValue *GV = MO.getGlobal(); 0
303 getSymbol(GV)->print(O, MAI); 0
304 printOffset(MO.getOffset(), O); 0
305 } 0
306 ----
307 void PPCAsmPrinter::printOperand(const MachineInstr *MI, unsigned OpNo, 0
308 raw_ostream &O) { ----
309 const DataLayout &DL = getDataLayout(); 0
310 const MachineOperand &MO = MI->getOperand(OpNo); 0
311 ----
312 switch (MO.getType()) { 0
313 case MachineOperand::MO_Register: { 0
314 // The MI is INLINEASM ONLY and UseVSXReg is always false. ----
315 const char *RegName = PPCInstPrinter::getRegisterName(MO.getReg()); 0
316 ----
317 // Linux assembler (Others?) does not take register mnemonics. ----
318 // FIXME - What about special registers used in mfspr/mtspr? ----
319 O << PPCRegisterInfo::stripRegisterPrefix(RegName); 0
320 return; 0
321 } ----
322 case MachineOperand::MO_Immediate: 0
323 O << MO.getImm(); 0
324 return; 0
325 ----
326 case MachineOperand::MO_MachineBasicBlock: 0
327 MO.getMBB()->getSymbol()->print(O, MAI); 0
328 return; 0
329 case MachineOperand::MO_ConstantPoolIndex: 0
330 O << DL.getPrivateGlobalPrefix() << "CPI" << getFunctionNumber() << '_' 0
331 << MO.getIndex(); 0
332 return; 0
333 case MachineOperand::MO_BlockAddress: 0
334 GetBlockAddressSymbol(MO.getBlockAddress())->print(O, MAI); 0
335 return; 0
336 case MachineOperand::MO_GlobalAddress: { 0
337 PrintSymbolOperand(MO, O); 0
338 return; 0
339 } ----
340 ----
341 default: 0
342 O << ""; 0
343 return; 0
344 } ----
345 } ----

347 /// PrintAsmOperand - Print out an operand for an inline asm expression. ----
348 /// ----
349 bool PPCAsmPrinter::PrintAsmOperand(const MachineInstr *MI, unsigned OpNo, 0
350 const char *ExtraCode, raw_ostream &O) { ----
351 // Does this asm operand have a single letter operand modifier? ----
352 if (ExtraCode && ExtraCode[0]) { 0
353 if (ExtraCode[1] != 0) return true; // Unknown modifier. 0
354 ----
355 switch (ExtraCode[0]) { 0
356 default: 0
357 // See if this is a generic print operand ----
358 return AsmPrinter::PrintAsmOperand(MI, OpNo, ExtraCode, O); 0
359 case 'L': // Write second word of DImode reference. 0
360 // Verify that this operand has two consecutive registers. ----
361 if (!MI->getOperand(OpNo).isReg() || 0
362 OpNo+1 == MI->getNumOperands() || 0
363 !MI->getOperand(OpNo+1).isReg()) 0
364 return true; 0
365 ++OpNo; // Return the high-part. 0
366 break; 0
367 case 'I': 0
368 // Write 'i' if an integer constant, otherwise nothing. Used to print ----
369 // addi vs add, etc. ----
370 if (MI->getOperand(OpNo).isImm()) 0
371 O << "i"; 0
372 return false; 0
373 case 'x': 0
374 if(!MI->getOperand(OpNo).isReg()) 0
375 return true; 0
376 // This operand uses VSX numbering. ----
377 // If the operand is a VMX register, convert it to a VSX register. ----
378 Register Reg = MI->getOperand(OpNo).getReg(); 0
379 if (PPCInstrInfo::isVRRegister(Reg)) 0
380 Reg = PPC::VSX32 + (Reg - PPC::V0); 0
381 else if (PPCInstrInfo::isVFRegister(Reg)) 0
382 Reg = PPC::VSX32 + (Reg - PPC::VF0); 0
383 const char *RegName; ----
384 RegName = PPCInstPrinter::getRegisterName(Reg); 0
385 RegName = PPCRegisterInfo::stripRegisterPrefix(RegName); 0
386 O << RegName; 0
387 return false; 0
388 } ----
389 } ----
390 ----
391 printOperand(MI, OpNo, O); 0
392 return false; 0
393 } ----
394 ----
395 // At the moment, all inline asm memory operands are a single register. ----
396 // In any case, the output of this routine should always be just one ----
397 // assembler operand. ----
398 bool PPCAsmPrinter::PrintAsmMemoryOperand(const MachineInstr *MI, unsigned OpNo, 0
399 const char *ExtraCode, ----
400 raw_ostream &O) { ----
401 if (ExtraCode && ExtraCode[0]) { 0
402 if (ExtraCode[1] != 0) return true; // Unknown modifier. 0
403 ----
404 switch (ExtraCode[0]) { 0
405 default: return true; // Unknown modifier. 0
406 case 'L': // A memory reference to the upper word of a double word op. 0
407 O << getDataLayout().getPointerSize() << "("; 0
408 printOperand(MI, OpNo, O); 0
409 O << ")"; 0
410 return false; 0
411 case 'y': // A memory reference for an X-form instruction 0
412 O << "0, "; 0
413 printOperand(MI, OpNo, O); 0
414 return false; 0
415 case 'I': 0
416 // Write 'i' if an integer constant, otherwise nothing. Used to print ----
417 // addi vs add, etc. ----
418 if (MI->getOperand(OpNo).isImm()) 0
419 O << "i"; 0
420 return false; 0
421 case 'U': // Print 'u' for update form. 0
422 case 'X': // Print 'x' for indexed form. ----
423 // FIXME: Currently for PowerPC memory operands are always loaded ----
424 // into a register, so we never get an update or indexed form. ----
425 // This is bad even for offset forms, since even if we know we ----
426 // have a value in -16(r1), we will generate a load into r ----
427 // and then load from 0(r). Until that issue is fixed, ----
428 // tolerate 'U' and 'X' but don't output anything. ----
429 assert(MI->getOperand(OpNo).isReg()); 0
430 return false; 0
431 } ----
432 } ----
433 ----
434 assert(MI->getOperand(OpNo).isReg()); 0
435 O << "0("; 0
436 printOperand(MI, OpNo, O); 0
437 O << ")"; 0
438 return false; 0
439 } ----

441 static void collectTOCStats(PPCAsmPrinter::TOCEntryType Type) { 0
442 ++NumTOCEntries; 0
443 switch (Type) { 0
444 case PPCAsmPrinter::TOCType_ConstantPool: 0
445 ++NumTOCConstPool; 0
446 break; 0
447 case PPCAsmPrinter::TOCType_GlobalInternal: 0
448 ++NumTOCGlobalInternal; 0
449 break; 0
450 case PPCAsmPrinter::TOCType_GlobalExternal: 0
451 ++NumTOCGlobalExternal; 0
452 break; 0
453 case PPCAsmPrinter::TOCType_JumpTable: 0
454 ++NumTOCJumpTable; 0
455 break; 0
456 case PPCAsmPrinter::TOCType_ThreadLocal: 0
457 ++NumTOCThreadLocal; 0
458 break; 0
459 case PPCAsmPrinter::TOCType_BlockAddress: 0
460 ++NumTOCBlockAddress; 0
461 break; 0
462 case PPCAsmPrinter::TOCType_EHBlock: 0
463 ++NumTOCEHBlock; 0
464 break; 0
465 } ----
466 } 0

468 /// lookUpOrCreateTOCEntry -- Given a symbol, look up whether a TOC entry ----
469 /// exists for it. If not, create one. Then return a symbol that references ----
470 /// the TOC entry. ----
471 MCSymbol * ----
472 PPCAsmPrinter::lookUpOrCreateTOCEntry(const MCSymbol *Sym, TOCEntryType Type, 0
473 MCSymbolRefExpr::VariantKind Kind) { ----
474 // If this is a new TOC entry add statistics about it. ----
475 if (!TOC.contains({Sym, Kind})) 0
476 collectTOCStats(Type); 0
477 ----
478 MCSymbol *&TOCEntry = TOC[{Sym, Kind}]; 0
479 if (!TOCEntry) 0
480 TOCEntry = createTempSymbol("C"); 0
481 return TOCEntry; 0
482 } ----
483 ----
484 void PPCAsmPrinter::LowerSTACKMAP(StackMaps &SM, const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
485 unsigned NumNOPBytes = MI.getOperand(1).getImm(); 0
486 ----
487 auto &Ctx = OutStreamer->getContext(); 0
488 MCSymbol *MILabel = Ctx.createTempSymbol(); 0
489 OutStreamer->emitLabel(MILabel); 0
490 ----
491 SM.recordStackMap(*MILabel, MI); 0
492 assert(NumNOPBytes % 4 == 0 && "Invalid number of NOP bytes requested!"); 0
493 ----
494 // Scan ahead to trim the shadow. ----
495 const MachineBasicBlock &MBB = *MI.getParent(); 0
496 MachineBasicBlock::const_iterator MII(MI); 0
497 ++MII; 0
498 while (NumNOPBytes > 0) { 0
499 if (MII == MBB.end() || MII->isCall() || 0
500 MII->getOpcode() == PPC::DBG_VALUE || 0
501 MII->getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::PATCHPOINT || 0
502 MII->getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::STACKMAP) 0
503 break; 0
504 ++MII; 0
505 NumNOPBytes -= 4; 0
506 } ----
507 ----
508 // Emit nops. ----
509 for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumNOPBytes; i += 4) 0
510 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(PPC::NOP)); 0
511 } 0
512 ----
513 // Lower a patchpoint of the form: ----
514 // [], , , , ----
515 void PPCAsmPrinter::LowerPATCHPOINT(StackMaps &SM, const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
516 auto &Ctx = OutStreamer->getContext(); 0
517 MCSymbol *MILabel = Ctx.createTempSymbol(); 0
518 OutStreamer->emitLabel(MILabel); 0
519 ----
520 SM.recordPatchPoint(*MILabel, MI); 0
521 PatchPointOpers Opers(&MI); 0
522 ----
523 unsigned EncodedBytes = 0; 0
524 const MachineOperand &CalleeMO = Opers.getCallTarget(); 0
525 ----
526 if (CalleeMO.isImm()) { 0
527 int64_t CallTarget = CalleeMO.getImm(); 0
528 if (CallTarget) { 0
529 assert((CallTarget & 0xFFFFFFFFFFFF) == CallTarget && 0
530 "High 16 bits of call target should be zero."); ----
531 Register ScratchReg = MI.getOperand(Opers.getNextScratchIdx()).getReg(); 0
532 EncodedBytes = 0; 0
533 // Materialize the jump address: ----
534 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(PPC::LI8) 0
535 .addReg(ScratchReg) 0
536 .addImm((CallTarget >> 32) & 0xFFFF)); 0
537 ++EncodedBytes; 0
538 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(PPC::RLDIC) 0
539 .addReg(ScratchReg) 0
540 .addReg(ScratchReg) 0
541 .addImm(32).addImm(16)); 0
542 ++EncodedBytes; 0
543 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(PPC::ORIS8) 0
544 .addReg(ScratchReg) 0
545 .addReg(ScratchReg) 0
546 .addImm((CallTarget >> 16) & 0xFFFF)); 0
547 ++EncodedBytes; 0
548 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(PPC::ORI8) 0
549 .addReg(ScratchReg) 0
550 .addReg(ScratchReg) 0
551 .addImm(CallTarget & 0xFFFF)); 0
552 ----
553 // Save the current TOC pointer before the remote call. ----
554 int TOCSaveOffset = Subtarget->getFrameLowering()->getTOCSaveOffset(); 0
555 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(PPC::STD) 0
556 .addReg(PPC::X2) 0
557 .addImm(TOCSaveOffset) 0
558 .addReg(PPC::X1)); 0
559 ++EncodedBytes; 0
560 ----
561 // If we're on ELFv1, then we need to load the actual function pointer ----
562 // from the function descriptor. ----
563 if (!Subtarget->isELFv2ABI()) { 0
564 // Load the new TOC pointer and the function address, but not r11 ----
565 // (needing this is rare, and loading it here would prevent passing it ----
566 // via a 'nest' parameter. ----
567 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(PPC::LD) 0
568 .addReg(PPC::X2) 0
569 .addImm(8) 0
570 .addReg(ScratchReg)); 0
571 ++EncodedBytes; 0
572 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(PPC::LD) 0
573 .addReg(ScratchReg) 0
574 .addImm(0) 0
575 .addReg(ScratchReg)); 0
576 ++EncodedBytes; 0
577 } ----
578 ----
579 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(PPC::MTCTR8) 0
580 .addReg(ScratchReg)); 0
581 ++EncodedBytes; 0
582 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(PPC::BCTRL8)); 0
583 ++EncodedBytes; 0
584 ----
585 // Restore the TOC pointer after the call. ----
586 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(PPC::LD) 0
587 .addReg(PPC::X2) 0
588 .addImm(TOCSaveOffset) 0
589 .addReg(PPC::X1)); 0
590 ++EncodedBytes; 0
591 } ----
592 } else if (CalleeMO.isGlobal()) { 0
593 const GlobalValue *GValue = CalleeMO.getGlobal(); 0
594 MCSymbol *MOSymbol = getSymbol(GValue); 0
595 const MCExpr *SymVar = MCSymbolRefExpr::create(MOSymbol, OutContext); 0
596 ----
597 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(PPC::BL8_NOP) 0
598 .addExpr(SymVar)); 0
599 EncodedBytes += 2; 0
600 } ----
601 ----
602 // Each instruction is 4 bytes. ----
603 EncodedBytes *= 4; 0
604 ----
605 // Emit padding. ----
606 unsigned NumBytes = Opers.getNumPatchBytes(); 0
607 assert(NumBytes >= EncodedBytes && 0
608 "Patchpoint can't request size less than the length of a call."); ----
609 assert((NumBytes - EncodedBytes) % 4 == 0 && 0
610 "Invalid number of NOP bytes requested!"); ----
611 for (unsigned i = EncodedBytes; i < NumBytes; i += 4) 0
612 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(PPC::NOP)); 0
613 } 0
614 ----
615 /// This helper function creates the TlsGetAddr MCSymbol for AIX. We will ----
616 /// create the csect and use the qual-name symbol instead of creating just the ----
617 /// external symbol. ----
618 static MCSymbol *createMCSymbolForTlsGetAddr(MCContext &Ctx, unsigned MIOpc) { 0
619 StringRef SymName = ----
620 MIOpc == PPC::GETtlsTpointer32AIX ? ".__get_tpointer" : ".__tls_get_addr"; 0
621 return Ctx ----
622 .getXCOFFSection(SymName, SectionKind::getText(), ----
623 XCOFF::CsectProperties(XCOFF::XMC_PR, XCOFF::XTY_ER)) 0
624 ->getQualNameSymbol(); 0
625 } ----
626 ----
627 void PPCAsmPrinter::EmitAIXTlsCallHelper(const MachineInstr *MI) { 0
628 assert(Subtarget->isAIXABI() && 0
629 "Only expecting to emit calls to get the thread pointer on AIX!"); ----
630 ----
631 MCSymbol *TlsCall = createMCSymbolForTlsGetAddr(OutContext, MI->getOpcode()); 0
632 const MCExpr *TlsRef = ----
633 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(TlsCall, MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None, OutContext); 0
634 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(PPC::BLA).addExpr(TlsRef)); 0
635 return; 0
636 } ----
637 ----
638 /// EmitTlsCall -- Given a GETtls[ld]ADDR[32] instruction, print a ----
639 /// call to __tls_get_addr to the current output stream. ----
640 void PPCAsmPrinter::EmitTlsCall(const MachineInstr *MI, 0
641 MCSymbolRefExpr::VariantKind VK) { ----
642 MCSymbolRefExpr::VariantKind Kind = MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None; 0
643 unsigned Opcode = PPC::BL8_NOP_TLS; 0
644 ----
645 assert(MI->getNumOperands() >= 3 && "Expecting at least 3 operands from MI"); 0
646 if (MI->getOperand(2).getTargetFlags() == PPCII::MO_GOT_TLSGD_PCREL_FLAG || 0
647 MI->getOperand(2).getTargetFlags() == PPCII::MO_GOT_TLSLD_PCREL_FLAG) { 0
648 Kind = MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_PPC_NOTOC; 0
649 Opcode = PPC::BL8_NOTOC_TLS; 0
650 } ----
651 const Module *M = MF->getFunction().getParent(); 0
652 ----
653 assert(MI->getOperand(0).isReg() && 0
654 ((Subtarget->isPPC64() && MI->getOperand(0).getReg() == PPC::X3) || ----
655 (!Subtarget->isPPC64() && MI->getOperand(0).getReg() == PPC::R3)) && ----
656 "GETtls[ld]ADDR[32] must define GPR3"); ----
657 assert(MI->getOperand(1).isReg() && 0
658 ((Subtarget->isPPC64() && MI->getOperand(1).getReg() == PPC::X3) || ----
659 (!Subtarget->isPPC64() && MI->getOperand(1).getReg() == PPC::R3)) && ----
660 "GETtls[ld]ADDR[32] must read GPR3"); ----
661 ----
662 if (Subtarget->isAIXABI()) { 0
663 // On AIX, the variable offset should already be in R4 and the region handle ----
664 // should already be in R3. ----
665 // For TLSGD, which currently is the only supported access model, we only ----
666 // need to generate an absolute branch to .__tls_get_addr. ----
667 Register VarOffsetReg = Subtarget->isPPC64() ? PPC::X4 : PPC::R4; 0
668 (void)VarOffsetReg; ----
669 assert(MI->getOperand(2).isReg() && 0
670 MI->getOperand(2).getReg() == VarOffsetReg && ----
671 "GETtls[ld]ADDR[32] must read GPR4"); ----
672 EmitAIXTlsCallHelper(MI); 0
673 return; 0
674 } ----
675 ----
676 MCSymbol *TlsGetAddr = OutContext.getOrCreateSymbol("__tls_get_addr"); 0
677 ----
678 if (Subtarget->is32BitELFABI() && isPositionIndependent()) 0
679 Kind = MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_PLT; 0
680 ----
681 const MCExpr *TlsRef = ----
682 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(TlsGetAddr, Kind, OutContext); 0
683 ----
684 // Add 32768 offset to the symbol so we follow up the latest GOT/PLT ABI. ----
685 if (Kind == MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_PLT && Subtarget->isSecurePlt() && 0
686 M->getPICLevel() == PICLevel::BigPIC) 0
687 TlsRef = MCBinaryExpr::createAdd( 0
688 TlsRef, MCConstantExpr::create(32768, OutContext), OutContext); 0
689 const MachineOperand &MO = MI->getOperand(2); 0
690 const GlobalValue *GValue = MO.getGlobal(); 0
691 MCSymbol *MOSymbol = getSymbol(GValue); 0
692 const MCExpr *SymVar = MCSymbolRefExpr::create(MOSymbol, VK, OutContext); 0
693 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, 0
694 MCInstBuilder(Subtarget->isPPC64() ? Opcode 0
695 : (unsigned)PPC::BL_TLS) ----
696 .addExpr(TlsRef) 0
697 .addExpr(SymVar)); 0
698 } ----
699 ----
700 /// Map a machine operand for a TOC pseudo-machine instruction to its ----
701 /// corresponding MCSymbol. ----
702 static MCSymbol *getMCSymbolForTOCPseudoMO(const MachineOperand &MO, 0
703 AsmPrinter &AP) { ----
704 switch (MO.getType()) { 0
705 case MachineOperand::MO_GlobalAddress: 0
706 return AP.getSymbol(MO.getGlobal()); 0
707 case MachineOperand::MO_ConstantPoolIndex: 0
708 return AP.GetCPISymbol(MO.getIndex()); 0
709 case MachineOperand::MO_JumpTableIndex: 0
710 return AP.GetJTISymbol(MO.getIndex()); 0
711 case MachineOperand::MO_BlockAddress: 0
712 return AP.GetBlockAddressSymbol(MO.getBlockAddress()); 0
713 default: 0
714 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected operand type to get symbol."); 0
715 } ----
716 } ----
717 ----
718 static bool hasTLSFlag(const MachineOperand &MO) { 0
719 unsigned Flags = MO.getTargetFlags(); 0
720 if (Flags & PPCII::MO_TLSGD_FLAG || Flags & PPCII::MO_TPREL_FLAG || 0
721 Flags & PPCII::MO_TLSLD_FLAG || Flags & PPCII::MO_TLSGDM_FLAG) 0
722 return true; 0
723 ----
724 if (Flags == PPCII::MO_TPREL_LO || Flags == PPCII::MO_TPREL_HA || 0
725 Flags == PPCII::MO_DTPREL_LO || Flags == PPCII::MO_TLSLD_LO || 0
726 Flags == PPCII::MO_TLS) ----
727 return true; 0
728 ----
729 return false; 0
730 } ----
731 ----
732 static PPCAsmPrinter::TOCEntryType ----
733 getTOCEntryTypeForMO(const MachineOperand &MO) { 0
734 // Use the target flags to determine if this MO is Thread Local. ----
735 // If we don't do this it comes out as Global. ----
736 if (hasTLSFlag(MO)) 0
737 return PPCAsmPrinter::TOCType_ThreadLocal; 0
738 ----
739 switch (MO.getType()) { 0
740 case MachineOperand::MO_GlobalAddress: { 0
741 const GlobalValue *GlobalV = MO.getGlobal(); 0
742 GlobalValue::LinkageTypes Linkage = GlobalV->getLinkage(); 0
743 if (Linkage == GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage || 0
744 Linkage == GlobalValue::AvailableExternallyLinkage || 0
745 Linkage == GlobalValue::ExternalWeakLinkage) ----
746 return PPCAsmPrinter::TOCType_GlobalExternal; 0
747 ----
748 return PPCAsmPrinter::TOCType_GlobalInternal; 0
749 } ----
750 case MachineOperand::MO_ConstantPoolIndex: 0
751 return PPCAsmPrinter::TOCType_ConstantPool; 0
752 case MachineOperand::MO_JumpTableIndex: 0
753 return PPCAsmPrinter::TOCType_JumpTable; 0
754 case MachineOperand::MO_BlockAddress: 0
755 return PPCAsmPrinter::TOCType_BlockAddress; 0
756 default: 0
757 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected operand type to get TOC type."); 0
758 } ----
759 } ----
760 /// EmitInstruction -- Print out a single PowerPC MI in Darwin syntax to ----
761 /// the current output stream. ----
762 /// ----
763 void PPCAsmPrinter::emitInstruction(const MachineInstr *MI) { 0
764 PPC_MC::verifyInstructionPredicates(MI->getOpcode(), 0
765 getSubtargetInfo().getFeatureBits()); 0
766 ----
767 MCInst TmpInst; 0
768 const bool IsPPC64 = Subtarget->isPPC64(); 0
769 const bool IsAIX = Subtarget->isAIXABI(); 0
770 const Module *M = MF->getFunction().getParent(); 0
771 PICLevel::Level PL = M->getPICLevel(); 0
772 ----
773 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
774 // Validate that SPE and FPU are mutually exclusive in codegen ----
775 if (!MI->isInlineAsm()) { 0
776 for (const MachineOperand &MO: MI->operands()) { 0
777 if (MO.isReg()) { 0
778 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
779 if (Subtarget->hasSPE()) { 0
780 if (PPC::F4RCRegClass.contains(Reg) || 0
781 PPC::F8RCRegClass.contains(Reg) || 0
782 PPC::VFRCRegClass.contains(Reg) || 0
783 PPC::VRRCRegClass.contains(Reg) || 0
784 PPC::VSFRCRegClass.contains(Reg) || 0
785 PPC::VSSRCRegClass.contains(Reg) 0
786 ) ----
787 llvm_unreachable("SPE targets cannot have FPRegs!"); 0
788 } else { ----
789 if (PPC::SPERCRegClass.contains(Reg)) 0
790 llvm_unreachable("SPE register found in FPU-targeted code!"); 0
791 } ----
792 } ----
793 } ----
794 } ----
795 #endif ----
796 ----
797 auto getTOCRelocAdjustedExprForXCOFF = [this](const MCExpr *Expr, 0
798 ptrdiff_t OriginalOffset) { 0
799 // Apply an offset to the TOC-based expression such that the adjusted ----
800 // notional offset from the TOC base (to be encoded into the instruction's D ----
801 // or DS field) is the signed 16-bit truncation of the original notional ----
802 // offset from the TOC base. ----
803 // This is consistent with the treatment used both by XL C/C++ and ----
804 // by AIX ld -r. ----
805 ptrdiff_t Adjustment = ----
806 OriginalOffset - llvm::SignExtend32<16>(OriginalOffset); 0
807 return MCBinaryExpr::createAdd( 0
808 Expr, MCConstantExpr::create(-Adjustment, OutContext), OutContext); 0
809 }; 0
810 ----
811 auto getTOCEntryLoadingExprForXCOFF = ----
812 [IsPPC64, getTOCRelocAdjustedExprForXCOFF, 0
813 this](const MCSymbol *MOSymbol, const MCExpr *Expr, ----
814 MCSymbolRefExpr::VariantKind VK = ----
815 MCSymbolRefExpr::VariantKind::VK_None) -> const MCExpr * { 0
816 const unsigned EntryByteSize = IsPPC64 ? 8 : 4; 0
817 const auto TOCEntryIter = TOC.find({MOSymbol, VK}); 0
818 assert(TOCEntryIter != TOC.end() && 0
819 "Could not find the TOC entry for this symbol."); ----
820 const ptrdiff_t EntryDistanceFromTOCBase = ----
821 (TOCEntryIter - TOC.begin()) * EntryByteSize; 0
822 constexpr int16_t PositiveTOCRange = INT16_MAX; 0
823 ----
824 if (EntryDistanceFromTOCBase > PositiveTOCRange) 0
825 return getTOCRelocAdjustedExprForXCOFF(Expr, EntryDistanceFromTOCBase); 0
826 ----
827 return Expr; 0
828 }; 0
829 auto GetVKForMO = [&](const MachineOperand &MO) { 0
830 // For TLS local-exec accesses on AIX, we have one TOC entry for the symbol ----
831 // (with the variable offset), which is differentiated by MO_TPREL_FLAG. ----
832 if (MO.getTargetFlags() & PPCII::MO_TPREL_FLAG) { 0
833 // TODO: Update the query and the comment above to add a check for initial ----
834 // exec when this TLS model is supported on AIX in the future, as both ----
835 // local-exec and initial-exec can use MO_TPREL_FLAG. ----
836 assert(MO.isGlobal() && "Only expecting a global MachineOperand here!\n"); 0
837 TLSModel::Model Model = TM.getTLSModel(MO.getGlobal()); 0
838 if (Model == TLSModel::LocalExec) 0
839 return MCSymbolRefExpr::VariantKind::VK_PPC_AIX_TLSLE; 0
840 llvm_unreachable("Only expecting local-exec accesses!"); 0
841 } ----
842 // For GD TLS access on AIX, we have two TOC entries for the symbol (one for ----
843 // the variable offset and the other for the region handle). They are ----
844 // differentiated by MO_TLSGD_FLAG and MO_TLSGDM_FLAG. ----
845 if (MO.getTargetFlags() & PPCII::MO_TLSGDM_FLAG) 0
846 return MCSymbolRefExpr::VariantKind::VK_PPC_AIX_TLSGDM; 0
847 if (MO.getTargetFlags() & PPCII::MO_TLSGD_FLAG) 0
848 return MCSymbolRefExpr::VariantKind::VK_PPC_AIX_TLSGD; 0
849 return MCSymbolRefExpr::VariantKind::VK_None; 0
850 }; 0
851 ----
852 // Lower multi-instruction pseudo operations. ----
853 switch (MI->getOpcode()) { 0
854 default: break; 0
855 case TargetOpcode::DBG_VALUE: 0
856 llvm_unreachable("Should be handled target independently"); 0
857 case TargetOpcode::STACKMAP: 0
858 return LowerSTACKMAP(SM, *MI); 0
859 case TargetOpcode::PATCHPOINT: 0
860 return LowerPATCHPOINT(SM, *MI); 0
861 ----
862 case PPC::MoveGOTtoLR: { 0
863 // Transform %lr = MoveGOTtoLR ----
864 // Into this: bl _GLOBAL_OFFSET_TABLE_@local-4 ----
865 // _GLOBAL_OFFSET_TABLE_@local-4 (instruction preceding ----
866 // _GLOBAL_OFFSET_TABLE_) has exactly one instruction: ----
867 // blrl ----
868 // This will return the pointer to _GLOBAL_OFFSET_TABLE_@local ----
869 MCSymbol *GOTSymbol = ----
870 OutContext.getOrCreateSymbol(StringRef("_GLOBAL_OFFSET_TABLE_")); 0
871 const MCExpr *OffsExpr = ----
872 MCBinaryExpr::createSub(MCSymbolRefExpr::create(GOTSymbol, 0
873 MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_PPC_LOCAL, ----
874 OutContext), ----
875 MCConstantExpr::create(4, OutContext), 0
876 OutContext); ----
877 ----
878 // Emit the 'bl'. ----
879 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(PPC::BL).addExpr(OffsExpr)); 0
880 return; 0
881 } ----
882 case PPC::MovePCtoLR: 0
883 case PPC::MovePCtoLR8: { ----
884 // Transform %lr = MovePCtoLR ----
885 // Into this, where the label is the PIC base: ----
886 // bl L1$pb ----
887 // L1$pb: ----
888 MCSymbol *PICBase = MF->getPICBaseSymbol(); 0
889 ----
890 // Emit the 'bl'. ----
891 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, 0
892 MCInstBuilder(PPC::BL) 0
893 // FIXME: We would like an efficient form for this, so we ----
894 // don't have to do a lot of extra uniquing. ----
895 .addExpr(MCSymbolRefExpr::create(PICBase, OutContext))); 0
896 ----
897 // Emit the label. ----
898 OutStreamer->emitLabel(PICBase); 0
899 return; 0
900 } ----
901 case PPC::UpdateGBR: { 0
902 // Transform %rd = UpdateGBR(%rt, %ri) ----
903 // Into: lwz %rt, .L0$poff - .L0$pb(%ri) ----
904 // add %rd, %rt, %ri ----
905 // or into (if secure plt mode is on): ----
906 // addis r30, r30, {.LTOC,_GLOBAL_OFFSET_TABLE} - .L0$pb@ha ----
907 // addi r30, r30, {.LTOC,_GLOBAL_OFFSET_TABLE} - .L0$pb@l ----
908 // Get the offset from the GOT Base Register to the GOT ----
909 LowerPPCMachineInstrToMCInst(MI, TmpInst, *this); 0
910 if (Subtarget->isSecurePlt() && isPositionIndependent() ) { 0
911 unsigned PICR = TmpInst.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
912 MCSymbol *BaseSymbol = OutContext.getOrCreateSymbol( 0
913 M->getPICLevel() == PICLevel::SmallPIC ? "_GLOBAL_OFFSET_TABLE_" 0
914 : ".LTOC"); ----
915 const MCExpr *PB = ----
916 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(MF->getPICBaseSymbol(), OutContext); 0
917 ----
918 const MCExpr *DeltaExpr = MCBinaryExpr::createSub( 0
919 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(BaseSymbol, OutContext), PB, OutContext); 0
920 ----
921 const MCExpr *DeltaHi = PPCMCExpr::createHa(DeltaExpr, OutContext); 0
922 EmitToStreamer( 0
923 *OutStreamer, 0
924 MCInstBuilder(PPC::ADDIS).addReg(PICR).addReg(PICR).addExpr(DeltaHi)); 0
925 ----
926 const MCExpr *DeltaLo = PPCMCExpr::createLo(DeltaExpr, OutContext); 0
927 EmitToStreamer( 0
928 *OutStreamer, 0
929 MCInstBuilder(PPC::ADDI).addReg(PICR).addReg(PICR).addExpr(DeltaLo)); 0
930 return; 0
931 } else { ----
932 MCSymbol *PICOffset = ----
933 MF->getInfo()->getPICOffsetSymbol(*MF); 0
934 TmpInst.setOpcode(PPC::LWZ); 0
935 const MCExpr *Exp = ----
936 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(PICOffset, MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None, OutContext); 0
937 const MCExpr *PB = ----
938 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(MF->getPICBaseSymbol(), 0
939 MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None, ----
940 OutContext); ----
941 const MCOperand TR = TmpInst.getOperand(1); 0
942 const MCOperand PICR = TmpInst.getOperand(0); 0
943 ----
944 // Step 1: lwz %rt, .L$poff - .L$pb(%ri) ----
945 TmpInst.getOperand(1) = 0
946 MCOperand::createExpr(MCBinaryExpr::createSub(Exp, PB, OutContext)); 0
947 TmpInst.getOperand(0) = TR; 0
948 TmpInst.getOperand(2) = PICR; 0
949 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, TmpInst); 0
950 ----
951 TmpInst.setOpcode(PPC::ADD4); 0
952 TmpInst.getOperand(0) = PICR; 0
953 TmpInst.getOperand(1) = TR; 0
954 TmpInst.getOperand(2) = PICR; 0
955 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, TmpInst); 0
956 return; 0
957 } ----
958 } ----
959 case PPC::LWZtoc: { 0
960 // Transform %rN = LWZtoc @op1, %r2 ----
961 LowerPPCMachineInstrToMCInst(MI, TmpInst, *this); 0
962 ----
963 // Change the opcode to LWZ. ----
964 TmpInst.setOpcode(PPC::LWZ); 0
965 ----
966 const MachineOperand &MO = MI->getOperand(1); 0
967 assert((MO.isGlobal() || MO.isCPI() || MO.isJTI() || MO.isBlockAddress()) && 0
968 "Invalid operand for LWZtoc."); ----
969 ----
970 // Map the operand to its corresponding MCSymbol. ----
971 const MCSymbol *const MOSymbol = getMCSymbolForTOCPseudoMO(MO, *this); 0
972 ----
973 // Create a reference to the GOT entry for the symbol. The GOT entry will be ----
974 // synthesized later. ----
975 if (PL == PICLevel::SmallPIC && !IsAIX) { 0
976 const MCExpr *Exp = ----
977 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(MOSymbol, MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_GOT, 0
978 OutContext); ----
979 TmpInst.getOperand(1) = MCOperand::createExpr(Exp); 0
980 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, TmpInst); 0
981 return; 0
982 } ----
983 ----
984 MCSymbolRefExpr::VariantKind VK = GetVKForMO(MO); 0
985 ----
986 // Otherwise, use the TOC. 'TOCEntry' is a label used to reference the ----
987 // storage allocated in the TOC which contains the address of ----
988 // 'MOSymbol'. Said TOC entry will be synthesized later. ----
989 MCSymbol *TOCEntry = ----
990 lookUpOrCreateTOCEntry(MOSymbol, getTOCEntryTypeForMO(MO), VK); 0
991 const MCExpr *Exp = ----
992 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(TOCEntry, MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None, OutContext); 0
993 ----
994 // AIX uses the label directly as the lwz displacement operand for ----
995 // references into the toc section. The displacement value will be generated ----
996 // relative to the toc-base. ----
997 if (IsAIX) { 0
998 assert( 0
999 TM.getCodeModel() == CodeModel::Small && ----
1000 "This pseudo should only be selected for 32-bit small code model."); ----
1001 Exp = getTOCEntryLoadingExprForXCOFF(MOSymbol, Exp, VK); 0
1002 TmpInst.getOperand(1) = MCOperand::createExpr(Exp); 0
1003 ----
1004 // Print MO for better readability ----
1005 if (isVerbose()) 0
1006 OutStreamer->getCommentOS() << MO << '\n'; 0
1007 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, TmpInst); 0
1008 return; 0
1009 } ----
1010 ----
1011 // Create an explicit subtract expression between the local symbol and ----
1012 // '.LTOC' to manifest the toc-relative offset. ----
1013 const MCExpr *PB = MCSymbolRefExpr::create( 0
1014 OutContext.getOrCreateSymbol(Twine(".LTOC")), OutContext); 0
1015 Exp = MCBinaryExpr::createSub(Exp, PB, OutContext); 0
1016 TmpInst.getOperand(1) = MCOperand::createExpr(Exp); 0
1017 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, TmpInst); 0
1018 return; 0
1019 } ----
1020 case PPC::ADDItoc: 0
1021 case PPC::ADDItoc8: { ----
1022 assert(IsAIX && TM.getCodeModel() == CodeModel::Small && 0
1023 "PseudoOp only valid for small code model AIX"); ----
1024 ----
1025 // Transform %rN = ADDItoc/8 @op1, %r2. ----
1026 LowerPPCMachineInstrToMCInst(MI, TmpInst, *this); 0
1027 ----
1028 // Change the opcode to load address. ----
1029 TmpInst.setOpcode((!IsPPC64) ? (PPC::LA) : (PPC::LA8)); 0
1030 ----
1031 const MachineOperand &MO = MI->getOperand(1); 0
1032 assert(MO.isGlobal() && "Invalid operand for ADDItoc[8]."); 0
1033 ----
1034 // Map the operand to its corresponding MCSymbol. ----
1035 const MCSymbol *const MOSymbol = getMCSymbolForTOCPseudoMO(MO, *this); 0
1036 ----
1037 const MCExpr *Exp = ----
1038 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(MOSymbol, MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None, OutContext); 0
1039 ----
1040 TmpInst.getOperand(1) = TmpInst.getOperand(2); 0
1041 TmpInst.getOperand(2) = MCOperand::createExpr(Exp); 0
1042 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, TmpInst); 0
1043 return; 0
1044 } ----
1045 case PPC::LDtocJTI: 0
1046 case PPC::LDtocCPT: ----
1047 case PPC::LDtocBA: ----
1048 case PPC::LDtoc: { ----
1049 // Transform %x3 = LDtoc @min1, %x2 ----
1050 LowerPPCMachineInstrToMCInst(MI, TmpInst, *this); 0
1051 ----
1052 // Change the opcode to LD. ----
1053 TmpInst.setOpcode(PPC::LD); 0
1054 ----
1055 const MachineOperand &MO = MI->getOperand(1); 0
1056 assert((MO.isGlobal() || MO.isCPI() || MO.isJTI() || MO.isBlockAddress()) && 0
1057 "Invalid operand!"); ----
1058 ----
1059 // Map the operand to its corresponding MCSymbol. ----
1060 const MCSymbol *const MOSymbol = getMCSymbolForTOCPseudoMO(MO, *this); 0
1061 ----
1062 MCSymbolRefExpr::VariantKind VK = GetVKForMO(MO); 0
1063 ----
1064 // Map the machine operand to its corresponding MCSymbol, then map the ----
1065 // global address operand to be a reference to the TOC entry we will ----
1066 // synthesize later. ----
1067 MCSymbol *TOCEntry = ----
1068 lookUpOrCreateTOCEntry(MOSymbol, getTOCEntryTypeForMO(MO), VK); 0
1069 ----
1070 MCSymbolRefExpr::VariantKind VKExpr = 0
1071 IsAIX ? MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None : MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_PPC_TOC; 0
1072 const MCExpr *Exp = MCSymbolRefExpr::create(TOCEntry, VKExpr, OutContext); 0
1073 TmpInst.getOperand(1) = MCOperand::createExpr( 0
1074 IsAIX ? getTOCEntryLoadingExprForXCOFF(MOSymbol, Exp, VK) : Exp); 0
1075 ----
1076 // Print MO for better readability ----
1077 if (isVerbose() && IsAIX) 0
1078 OutStreamer->getCommentOS() << MO << '\n'; 0
1079 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, TmpInst); 0
1080 return; 0
1081 } ----
1082 case PPC::ADDIStocHA: { 0
1083 assert((IsAIX && !IsPPC64 && TM.getCodeModel() == CodeModel::Large) && 0
1084 "This pseudo should only be selected for 32-bit large code model on" ----
1085 " AIX."); ----
1086 ----
1087 // Transform %rd = ADDIStocHA %rA, @sym(%r2) ----
1088 LowerPPCMachineInstrToMCInst(MI, TmpInst, *this); 0
1089 ----
1090 // Change the opcode to ADDIS. ----
1091 TmpInst.setOpcode(PPC::ADDIS); 0
1092 ----
1093 const MachineOperand &MO = MI->getOperand(2); 0
1094 assert((MO.isGlobal() || MO.isCPI() || MO.isJTI() || MO.isBlockAddress()) && 0
1095 "Invalid operand for ADDIStocHA."); ----
1096 ----
1097 // Map the machine operand to its corresponding MCSymbol. ----
1098 MCSymbol *MOSymbol = getMCSymbolForTOCPseudoMO(MO, *this); 0
1099 ----
1100 MCSymbolRefExpr::VariantKind VK = GetVKForMO(MO); 0
1101 ----
1102 // Always use TOC on AIX. Map the global address operand to be a reference ----
1103 // to the TOC entry we will synthesize later. 'TOCEntry' is a label used to ----
1104 // reference the storage allocated in the TOC which contains the address of ----
1105 // 'MOSymbol'. ----
1106 MCSymbol *TOCEntry = ----
1107 lookUpOrCreateTOCEntry(MOSymbol, getTOCEntryTypeForMO(MO), VK); 0
1108 const MCExpr *Exp = MCSymbolRefExpr::create(TOCEntry, 0
1109 MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_PPC_U, ----
1110 OutContext); ----
1111 TmpInst.getOperand(2) = MCOperand::createExpr(Exp); 0
1112 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, TmpInst); 0
1113 return; 0
1114 } ----
1115 case PPC::LWZtocL: { 0
1116 assert(IsAIX && !IsPPC64 && TM.getCodeModel() == CodeModel::Large && 0
1117 "This pseudo should only be selected for 32-bit large code model on" ----
1118 " AIX."); ----
1119 ----
1120 // Transform %rd = LWZtocL @sym, %rs. ----
1121 LowerPPCMachineInstrToMCInst(MI, TmpInst, *this); 0
1122 ----
1123 // Change the opcode to lwz. ----
1124 TmpInst.setOpcode(PPC::LWZ); 0
1125 ----
1126 const MachineOperand &MO = MI->getOperand(1); 0
1127 assert((MO.isGlobal() || MO.isCPI() || MO.isJTI() || MO.isBlockAddress()) && 0
1128 "Invalid operand for LWZtocL."); ----
1129 ----
1130 // Map the machine operand to its corresponding MCSymbol. ----
1131 MCSymbol *MOSymbol = getMCSymbolForTOCPseudoMO(MO, *this); 0
1132 ----
1133 MCSymbolRefExpr::VariantKind VK = GetVKForMO(MO); 0
1134 ----
1135 // Always use TOC on AIX. Map the global address operand to be a reference ----
1136 // to the TOC entry we will synthesize later. 'TOCEntry' is a label used to ----
1137 // reference the storage allocated in the TOC which contains the address of ----
1138 // 'MOSymbol'. ----
1139 MCSymbol *TOCEntry = ----
1140 lookUpOrCreateTOCEntry(MOSymbol, getTOCEntryTypeForMO(MO), VK); 0
1141 const MCExpr *Exp = MCSymbolRefExpr::create(TOCEntry, 0
1142 MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_PPC_L, ----
1143 OutContext); ----
1144 TmpInst.getOperand(1) = MCOperand::createExpr(Exp); 0
1145 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, TmpInst); 0
1146 return; 0
1147 } ----
1148 case PPC::ADDIStocHA8: { 0
1149 // Transform %xd = ADDIStocHA8 %x2, @sym ----
1150 LowerPPCMachineInstrToMCInst(MI, TmpInst, *this); 0
1151 ----
1152 // Change the opcode to ADDIS8. If the global address is the address of ----
1153 // an external symbol, is a jump table address, is a block address, or is a ----
1154 // constant pool index with large code model enabled, then generate a TOC ----
1155 // entry and reference that. Otherwise, reference the symbol directly. ----
1156 TmpInst.setOpcode(PPC::ADDIS8); 0
1157 ----
1158 const MachineOperand &MO = MI->getOperand(2); 0
1159 assert((MO.isGlobal() || MO.isCPI() || MO.isJTI() || MO.isBlockAddress()) && 0
1160 "Invalid operand for ADDIStocHA8!"); ----
1161 ----
1162 const MCSymbol *MOSymbol = getMCSymbolForTOCPseudoMO(MO, *this); 0
1163 ----
1164 MCSymbolRefExpr::VariantKind VK = GetVKForMO(MO); 0
1165 ----
1166 const bool GlobalToc = ----
1167 MO.isGlobal() && Subtarget->isGVIndirectSymbol(MO.getGlobal()); 0
1168 if (GlobalToc || MO.isJTI() || MO.isBlockAddress() || 0
1169 (MO.isCPI() && TM.getCodeModel() == CodeModel::Large)) 0
1170 MOSymbol = lookUpOrCreateTOCEntry(MOSymbol, getTOCEntryTypeForMO(MO), VK); 0
1171 ----
1172 VK = IsAIX ? MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_PPC_U : MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_PPC_TOC_HA; 0
1173 ----
1174 const MCExpr *Exp = ----
1175 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(MOSymbol, VK, OutContext); 0
1176 ----
1177 if (!MO.isJTI() && MO.getOffset()) 0
1178 Exp = MCBinaryExpr::createAdd(Exp, 0
1179 MCConstantExpr::create(MO.getOffset(), 0
1180 OutContext), ----
1181 OutContext); ----
1182 ----
1183 TmpInst.getOperand(2) = MCOperand::createExpr(Exp); 0
1184 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, TmpInst); 0
1185 return; 0
1186 } ----
1187 case PPC::LDtocL: { 0
1188 // Transform %xd = LDtocL @sym, %xs ----
1189 LowerPPCMachineInstrToMCInst(MI, TmpInst, *this); 0
1190 ----
1191 // Change the opcode to LD. If the global address is the address of ----
1192 // an external symbol, is a jump table address, is a block address, or is ----
1193 // a constant pool index with large code model enabled, then generate a ----
1194 // TOC entry and reference that. Otherwise, reference the symbol directly. ----
1195 TmpInst.setOpcode(PPC::LD); 0
1196 ----
1197 const MachineOperand &MO = MI->getOperand(1); 0
1198 assert((MO.isGlobal() || MO.isCPI() || MO.isJTI() || 0
1199 MO.isBlockAddress()) && ----
1200 "Invalid operand for LDtocL!"); ----
1201 ----
1202 LLVM_DEBUG(assert( 0
1203 (!MO.isGlobal() || Subtarget->isGVIndirectSymbol(MO.getGlobal())) && ----
1204 "LDtocL used on symbol that could be accessed directly is " ----
1205 "invalid. Must match ADDIStocHA8.")); ----
1206 ----
1207 const MCSymbol *MOSymbol = getMCSymbolForTOCPseudoMO(MO, *this); 0
1208 ----
1209 MCSymbolRefExpr::VariantKind VK = GetVKForMO(MO); 0
1210 ----
1211 if (!MO.isCPI() || TM.getCodeModel() == CodeModel::Large) 0
1212 MOSymbol = lookUpOrCreateTOCEntry(MOSymbol, getTOCEntryTypeForMO(MO), VK); 0
1213 ----
1214 VK = IsAIX ? MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_PPC_L : MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_PPC_TOC_LO; 0
1215 const MCExpr *Exp = ----
1216 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(MOSymbol, VK, OutContext); 0
1217 TmpInst.getOperand(1) = MCOperand::createExpr(Exp); 0
1218 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, TmpInst); 0
1219 return; 0
1220 } ----
1221 case PPC::ADDItocL: { 0
1222 // Transform %xd = ADDItocL %xs, @sym ----
1223 LowerPPCMachineInstrToMCInst(MI, TmpInst, *this); 0
1224 ----
1225 // Change the opcode to ADDI8. If the global address is external, then ----
1226 // generate a TOC entry and reference that. Otherwise, reference the ----
1227 // symbol directly. ----
1228 TmpInst.setOpcode(PPC::ADDI8); 0
1229 ----
1230 const MachineOperand &MO = MI->getOperand(2); 0
1231 assert((MO.isGlobal() || MO.isCPI()) && "Invalid operand for ADDItocL."); 0

1233 LLVM_DEBUG(assert( 0
1234 !(MO.isGlobal() && Subtarget->isGVIndirectSymbol(MO.getGlobal())) && ----
1235 "Interposable definitions must use indirect access.")); ----

1237 const MCExpr *Exp = ----
1238 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(getMCSymbolForTOCPseudoMO(MO, *this), 0
1239 MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_PPC_TOC_LO, OutContext); ----
1240 TmpInst.getOperand(2) = MCOperand::createExpr(Exp); 0
1241 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, TmpInst); 0
1242 return; 0
1243 } ----
1244 case PPC::ADDISgotTprelHA: { 0

1249 const GlobalValue *GValue = MO.getGlobal(); 0
1250 MCSymbol *MOSymbol = getSymbol(GValue); 0

1252 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(MOSymbol, MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_PPC_GOT_TPREL_HA, 0

1256 .addReg(MI->getOperand(1).getReg()) 0
1257 .addExpr(SymGotTprel)); 0
1258 return; 0
1259 } ----
1260 case PPC::LDgotTprelL: 0
1261 case PPC::LDgotTprelL32: { ----

1265 // Change the opcode to LD. ----

1278 ----
1279 case PPC::PPC32PICGOT: { 0
1280 MCSymbol *GOTSymbol = OutContext.getOrCreateSymbol(StringRef("_GLOBAL_OFFSET_TABLE_")); 0
1281 MCSymbol *GOTRef = OutContext.createTempSymbol(); 0
1282 MCSymbol *NextInstr = OutContext.createTempSymbol(); 0
1283 ----
1284 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(PPC::BL) 0
1285 // FIXME: We would like an efficient form for this, so we don't have to do ----
1286 // a lot of extra uniquing. ----
1287 .addExpr(MCSymbolRefExpr::create(NextInstr, OutContext))); 0

1289 MCBinaryExpr::createSub(MCSymbolRefExpr::create(GOTSymbol, OutContext), 0
1290 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(GOTRef, OutContext), 0
1291 OutContext); ----
1292 OutStreamer->emitLabel(GOTRef); 0
1293 OutStreamer->emitValue(OffsExpr, 4); 0
1294 OutStreamer->emitLabel(NextInstr); 0
1295 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(PPC::MFLR) 0
1296 .addReg(MI->getOperand(0).getReg())); 0
1297 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(PPC::LWZ) 0
1298 .addReg(MI->getOperand(1).getReg()) 0
1299 .addImm(0) 0
1300 .addReg(MI->getOperand(0).getReg())); 0
1301 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(PPC::ADD4) 0
1302 .addReg(MI->getOperand(0).getReg()) 0
1303 .addReg(MI->getOperand(1).getReg()) 0

1358 } ----
1359 case PPC::GETtlsADDR: 0

1367 // Unlike on Linux, there is no symbol or relocation needed for this call. ----

1379 } ----

1448 // Into: %rd = PADDI8 %rs, sym@dtprel ----
1449 const MachineOperand &MO = MI->getOperand(2); 0

1461 case PPC::ADDIdtprelL: 0
1462 // Transform: %xd = ADDIdtprelL %xs, @sym ----
1463 // Into: %xd = ADDI8 %xs, sym@dtprel@l ----
1464 case PPC::ADDIdtprelL32: { ----
1465 // Transform: %rd = ADDIdtprelL32 %rs, @sym ----
1466 // Into: %rd = ADDI %rs, sym@dtprel@l ----
1467 const MachineOperand &MO = MI->getOperand(2); 0
