1477 .addExpr(SymDtprel)); 0
1478 return; 0
1479 } ----
1480 case PPC::MFOCRF: 0
1481 case PPC::MFOCRF8: ----
1482 if (!Subtarget->hasMFOCRF()) { 0
1483 // Transform: %r3 = MFOCRF %cr7 ----
1484 // Into: %r3 = MFCR ;; cr7 ----
1485 unsigned NewOpcode = ----
1486 MI->getOpcode() == PPC::MFOCRF ? PPC::MFCR : PPC::MFCR8; 0
1487 OutStreamer->AddComment(PPCInstPrinter:: 0
1488 getRegisterName(MI->getOperand(1).getReg())); 0
1489 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(NewOpcode) 0
1490 .addReg(MI->getOperand(0).getReg())); 0
1491 return; 0
1492 } ----
1493 break; 0
1494 case PPC::MTOCRF: 0
1495 case PPC::MTOCRF8: ----
1496 if (!Subtarget->hasMFOCRF()) { 0
1497 // Transform: %cr7 = MTOCRF %r3 ----
1498 // Into: MTCRF mask, %r3 ;; cr7 ----
1499 unsigned NewOpcode = ----
1500 MI->getOpcode() == PPC::MTOCRF ? PPC::MTCRF : PPC::MTCRF8; 0
1501 unsigned Mask = 0x80 >> OutContext.getRegisterInfo() 0
1502 ->getEncodingValue(MI->getOperand(0).getReg()); 0
1503 OutStreamer->AddComment(PPCInstPrinter:: 0
1504 getRegisterName(MI->getOperand(0).getReg())); 0
1505 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(NewOpcode) 0
1506 .addImm(Mask) 0
1507 .addReg(MI->getOperand(1).getReg())); 0
1508 return; 0
1509 } ----
1510 break; 0
1511 case PPC::LD: 0
1512 case PPC::STD: ----
1513 case PPC::LWA_32: ----
1514 case PPC::LWA: { ----
1515 // Verify alignment is legal, so we don't create relocations ----
1516 // that can't be supported. ----
1517 unsigned OpNum = (MI->getOpcode() == PPC::STD) ? 2 : 1; 0
1518 const MachineOperand &MO = MI->getOperand(OpNum); 0
1519 if (MO.isGlobal()) { 0
1520 const DataLayout &DL = MO.getGlobal()->getParent()->getDataLayout(); 0
1521 if (MO.getGlobal()->getPointerAlignment(DL) < 4) 0
1522 llvm_unreachable("Global must be word-aligned for LD, STD, LWA!"); 0
1523 } ----
1524 // Now process the instruction normally. ----
1525 break; 0
1526 } ----
1527 case PPC::PseudoEIEIO: { 0
1528 EmitToStreamer( 0
1529 *OutStreamer, 0
1530 MCInstBuilder(PPC::ORI).addReg(PPC::X2).addReg(PPC::X2).addImm(0)); 0
1531 EmitToStreamer( 0
1532 *OutStreamer, 0
1533 MCInstBuilder(PPC::ORI).addReg(PPC::X2).addReg(PPC::X2).addImm(0)); 0
1534 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(PPC::EnforceIEIO)); 0
1535 return; 0
1536 } ----
1537 } ----
1538 ----
1539 LowerPPCMachineInstrToMCInst(MI, TmpInst, *this); 0
1540 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, TmpInst); 0
1541 } 0
1542 ----
1543 void PPCLinuxAsmPrinter::emitGNUAttributes(Module &M) { 0
1544 // Emit float ABI into GNU attribute ----
1545 Metadata *MD = M.getModuleFlag("float-abi"); 0
1546 MDString *FloatABI = dyn_cast_or_null(MD); 0
1547 if (!FloatABI) 0
1548 return; 0
1549 StringRef flt = FloatABI->getString(); 0
1550 // TODO: Support emitting soft-fp and hard double/single attributes. ----
1551 if (flt == "doubledouble") 0
1552 OutStreamer->emitGNUAttribute(Tag_GNU_Power_ABI_FP, 0
1553 Val_GNU_Power_ABI_HardFloat_DP | ----
1554 Val_GNU_Power_ABI_LDBL_IBM128); ----
1555 else if (flt == "ieeequad") 0
1556 OutStreamer->emitGNUAttribute(Tag_GNU_Power_ABI_FP, 0
1557 Val_GNU_Power_ABI_HardFloat_DP | ----
1558 Val_GNU_Power_ABI_LDBL_IEEE128); ----
1559 else if (flt == "ieeedouble") 0
1560 OutStreamer->emitGNUAttribute(Tag_GNU_Power_ABI_FP, 0
1561 Val_GNU_Power_ABI_HardFloat_DP | ----
1562 Val_GNU_Power_ABI_LDBL_64); ----
1563 } ----
1564 ----
1565 void PPCLinuxAsmPrinter::emitInstruction(const MachineInstr *MI) { 0
1566 if (!Subtarget->isPPC64()) 0
1567 return PPCAsmPrinter::emitInstruction(MI); 0
1568 ----
1569 switch (MI->getOpcode()) { 0
1570 default: 0
1571 return PPCAsmPrinter::emitInstruction(MI); 0
1572 case TargetOpcode::PATCHABLE_FUNCTION_ENTER: { 0
1573 // .begin: ----
1574 // b .end # lis 0, FuncId[16..32] ----
1575 // nop # li 0, FuncId[0..15] ----
1576 // std 0, -8(1) ----
1577 // mflr 0 ----
1578 // bl __xray_FunctionEntry ----
1579 // mtlr 0 ----
1580 // .end: ----
1581 // ----
1582 // Update compiler-rt/lib/xray/xray_powerpc64.cc accordingly when number ----
1583 // of instructions change. ----
1584 MCSymbol *BeginOfSled = OutContext.createTempSymbol(); 0
1585 MCSymbol *EndOfSled = OutContext.createTempSymbol(); 0
1586 OutStreamer->emitLabel(BeginOfSled); 0
1587 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, 0
1588 MCInstBuilder(PPC::B).addExpr( 0
1589 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(EndOfSled, OutContext))); 0
1590 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(PPC::NOP)); 0
1591 EmitToStreamer( 0
1592 *OutStreamer, 0
1593 MCInstBuilder(PPC::STD).addReg(PPC::X0).addImm(-8).addReg(PPC::X1)); 0
1594 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(PPC::MFLR8).addReg(PPC::X0)); 0
1595 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, 0
1596 MCInstBuilder(PPC::BL8_NOP) 0
1597 .addExpr(MCSymbolRefExpr::create( 0
1598 OutContext.getOrCreateSymbol("__xray_FunctionEntry"), 0
1599 OutContext))); ----
1600 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(PPC::MTLR8).addReg(PPC::X0)); 0
1601 OutStreamer->emitLabel(EndOfSled); 0
1602 recordSled(BeginOfSled, *MI, SledKind::FUNCTION_ENTER, 2); 0
1603 break; 0
1604 } ----
1605 case TargetOpcode::PATCHABLE_RET: { 0
1606 unsigned RetOpcode = MI->getOperand(0).getImm(); 0
1607 MCInst RetInst; 0
1608 RetInst.setOpcode(RetOpcode); 0
1609 for (const auto &MO : llvm::drop_begin(MI->operands())) { 0
1610 MCOperand MCOp; 0
1611 if (LowerPPCMachineOperandToMCOperand(MO, MCOp, *this)) 0
1612 RetInst.addOperand(MCOp); 0
1613 } ----
1614 ----
1615 bool IsConditional; ----
1616 if (RetOpcode == PPC::BCCLR) { 0
1617 IsConditional = true; 0
1618 } else if (RetOpcode == PPC::TCRETURNdi8 || RetOpcode == PPC::TCRETURNri8 || 0
1619 RetOpcode == PPC::TCRETURNai8) { ----
1620 break; ----
1621 } else if (RetOpcode == PPC::BLR8 || RetOpcode == PPC::TAILB8) { 0
1622 IsConditional = false; 0
1623 } else { ----
1624 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, RetInst); 0
1625 break; 0
1626 } ----
1627 ----
1628 MCSymbol *FallthroughLabel; ----
1629 if (IsConditional) { 0
1630 // Before: ----
1631 // bgtlr cr0 ----
1632 // ----
1633 // After: ----
1634 // ble cr0, .end ----
1635 // .p2align 3 ----
1636 // .begin: ----
1637 // blr # lis 0, FuncId[16..32] ----
1638 // nop # li 0, FuncId[0..15] ----
1639 // std 0, -8(1) ----
1640 // mflr 0 ----
1641 // bl __xray_FunctionExit ----
1642 // mtlr 0 ----
1643 // blr ----
1644 // .end: ----
1645 // ----
1646 // Update compiler-rt/lib/xray/xray_powerpc64.cc accordingly when number ----
1647 // of instructions change. ----
1648 FallthroughLabel = OutContext.createTempSymbol(); 0
1649 EmitToStreamer( 0
1650 *OutStreamer, 0
1651 MCInstBuilder(PPC::BCC) 0
1652 .addImm(PPC::InvertPredicate( 0
1653 static_cast(MI->getOperand(1).getImm()))) 0
1654 .addReg(MI->getOperand(2).getReg()) 0
1655 .addExpr(MCSymbolRefExpr::create(FallthroughLabel, OutContext))); 0
1656 RetInst = MCInst(); 0
1657 RetInst.setOpcode(PPC::BLR8); 0
1658 } ----
1659 // .p2align 3 ----
1660 // .begin: ----
1661 // b(lr)? # lis 0, FuncId[16..32] ----
1662 // nop # li 0, FuncId[0..15] ----
1663 // std 0, -8(1) ----
1664 // mflr 0 ----
1665 // bl __xray_FunctionExit ----
1666 // mtlr 0 ----
1667 // b(lr)? ----
1668 // ----
1669 // Update compiler-rt/lib/xray/xray_powerpc64.cc accordingly when number ----
1670 // of instructions change. ----
1671 OutStreamer->emitCodeAlignment(Align(8), &getSubtargetInfo()); 0
1672 MCSymbol *BeginOfSled = OutContext.createTempSymbol(); 0
1673 OutStreamer->emitLabel(BeginOfSled); 0
1674 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, RetInst); 0
1675 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(PPC::NOP)); 0
1676 EmitToStreamer( 0
1677 *OutStreamer, 0
1678 MCInstBuilder(PPC::STD).addReg(PPC::X0).addImm(-8).addReg(PPC::X1)); 0
1679 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(PPC::MFLR8).addReg(PPC::X0)); 0
1680 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, 0
1681 MCInstBuilder(PPC::BL8_NOP) 0
1682 .addExpr(MCSymbolRefExpr::create( 0
1683 OutContext.getOrCreateSymbol("__xray_FunctionExit"), 0
1684 OutContext))); ----
1685 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(PPC::MTLR8).addReg(PPC::X0)); 0
1686 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, RetInst); 0
1687 if (IsConditional) 0
1688 OutStreamer->emitLabel(FallthroughLabel); 0
1689 recordSled(BeginOfSled, *MI, SledKind::FUNCTION_EXIT, 2); 0
1690 break; 0
1691 } 0
1692 case TargetOpcode::PATCHABLE_FUNCTION_EXIT: 0
1693 llvm_unreachable("PATCHABLE_FUNCTION_EXIT should never be emitted"); 0
1694 case TargetOpcode::PATCHABLE_TAIL_CALL: 0
1695 // TODO: Define a trampoline `__xray_FunctionTailExit` and differentiate a ----
1696 // normal function exit from a tail exit. ----
1697 llvm_unreachable("Tail call is handled in the normal case. See comments " 0
1698 "around this assert."); ----
1699 } ----
1700 } ----
1701 ----
1702 void PPCLinuxAsmPrinter::emitStartOfAsmFile(Module &M) { 0
1703 if (static_cast(TM).isELFv2ABI()) { 0
1704 PPCTargetStreamer *TS = ----
1705 static_cast(OutStreamer->getTargetStreamer()); 0
1706 TS->emitAbiVersion(2); 0
1707 } ----
1708 ----
1709 if (static_cast(TM).isPPC64() || 0
1710 !isPositionIndependent()) 0
1711 return AsmPrinter::emitStartOfAsmFile(M); 0
1712 ----
1713 if (M.getPICLevel() == PICLevel::SmallPIC) 0
1714 return AsmPrinter::emitStartOfAsmFile(M); 0
1715 ----
1716 OutStreamer->switchSection(OutContext.getELFSection( 0
1717 ".got2", ELF::SHT_PROGBITS, ELF::SHF_WRITE | ELF::SHF_ALLOC)); ----
1718 ----
1719 MCSymbol *TOCSym = OutContext.getOrCreateSymbol(Twine(".LTOC")); 0
1720 MCSymbol *CurrentPos = OutContext.createTempSymbol(); 0
1721 ----
1722 OutStreamer->emitLabel(CurrentPos); 0
1723 ----
1724 // The GOT pointer points to the middle of the GOT, in order to reference the ----
1725 // entire 64kB range. 0x8000 is the midpoint. ----
1726 const MCExpr *tocExpr = ----
1727 MCBinaryExpr::createAdd(MCSymbolRefExpr::create(CurrentPos, OutContext), 0
1728 MCConstantExpr::create(0x8000, OutContext), 0
1729 OutContext); ----
1730 ----
1731 OutStreamer->emitAssignment(TOCSym, tocExpr); 0
1732 ----
1733 OutStreamer->switchSection(getObjFileLowering().getTextSection()); 0
1734 } ----
1735 ----
1736 void PPCLinuxAsmPrinter::emitFunctionEntryLabel() { 0
1737 // linux/ppc32 - Normal entry label. ----
1738 if (!Subtarget->isPPC64() && 0
1739 (!isPositionIndependent() || 0
1740 MF->getFunction().getParent()->getPICLevel() == PICLevel::SmallPIC)) 0
1741 return AsmPrinter::emitFunctionEntryLabel(); 0
1742 ----
1743 if (!Subtarget->isPPC64()) { 0
1744 const PPCFunctionInfo *PPCFI = MF->getInfo(); 0
1745 if (PPCFI->usesPICBase() && !Subtarget->isSecurePlt()) { 0
1746 MCSymbol *RelocSymbol = PPCFI->getPICOffsetSymbol(*MF); 0
1747 MCSymbol *PICBase = MF->getPICBaseSymbol(); 0
1748 OutStreamer->emitLabel(RelocSymbol); 0
1749 ----
1750 const MCExpr *OffsExpr = ----
1751 MCBinaryExpr::createSub( 0
1752 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(OutContext.getOrCreateSymbol(Twine(".LTOC")), 0
1753 OutContext), ----
1754 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(PICBase, OutContext), 0
1755 OutContext); ----
1756 OutStreamer->emitValue(OffsExpr, 4); 0
1757 OutStreamer->emitLabel(CurrentFnSym); 0
1758 return; 0
1759 } else ----
1760 return AsmPrinter::emitFunctionEntryLabel(); 0
1761 } ----
1762 ----
1763 // ELFv2 ABI - Normal entry label. ----
1764 if (Subtarget->isELFv2ABI()) { 0
1765 // In the Large code model, we allow arbitrary displacements between ----
1766 // the text section and its associated TOC section. We place the ----
1767 // full 8-byte offset to the TOC in memory immediately preceding ----
1768 // the function global entry point. ----
1769 if (TM.getCodeModel() == CodeModel::Large 0
1770 && !MF->getRegInfo().use_empty(PPC::X2)) { 0
1771 const PPCFunctionInfo *PPCFI = MF->getInfo(); 0
1772 ----
1773 MCSymbol *TOCSymbol = OutContext.getOrCreateSymbol(StringRef(".TOC.")); 0
1774 MCSymbol *GlobalEPSymbol = PPCFI->getGlobalEPSymbol(*MF); 0
1775 const MCExpr *TOCDeltaExpr = ----
1776 MCBinaryExpr::createSub(MCSymbolRefExpr::create(TOCSymbol, OutContext), 0
1777 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(GlobalEPSymbol, 0
1778 OutContext), ----
1779 OutContext); ----
1780 ----
1781 OutStreamer->emitLabel(PPCFI->getTOCOffsetSymbol(*MF)); 0
1782 OutStreamer->emitValue(TOCDeltaExpr, 8); 0
1783 } ----
1784 return AsmPrinter::emitFunctionEntryLabel(); 0
1785 } ----
1786 ----
1787 // Emit an official procedure descriptor. ----
1788 MCSectionSubPair Current = OutStreamer->getCurrentSection(); 0
1789 MCSectionELF *Section = OutStreamer->getContext().getELFSection( 0
1790 ".opd", ELF::SHT_PROGBITS, ELF::SHF_WRITE | ELF::SHF_ALLOC); ----
1791 OutStreamer->switchSection(Section); 0
1792 OutStreamer->emitLabel(CurrentFnSym); 0
1793 OutStreamer->emitValueToAlignment(Align(8)); 0
1794 MCSymbol *Symbol1 = CurrentFnSymForSize; 0
1795 // Generates a R_PPC64_ADDR64 (from FK_DATA_8) relocation for the function ----
1796 // entry point. ----
1797 OutStreamer->emitValue(MCSymbolRefExpr::create(Symbol1, OutContext), 0
1798 8 /*size*/); ----
1799 MCSymbol *Symbol2 = OutContext.getOrCreateSymbol(StringRef(".TOC.")); 0
1800 // Generates a R_PPC64_TOC relocation for TOC base insertion. ----
1801 OutStreamer->emitValue( 0
1802 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(Symbol2, MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_PPC_TOCBASE, OutContext), 0
1803 8/*size*/); ----
1804 // Emit a null environment pointer. ----
1805 OutStreamer->emitIntValue(0, 8 /* size */); 0
1806 OutStreamer->switchSection(Current.first, Current.second); 0
1807 } ----
1808 ----
1809 void PPCLinuxAsmPrinter::emitEndOfAsmFile(Module &M) { 0
1810 const DataLayout &DL = getDataLayout(); 0
1811 ----
1812 bool isPPC64 = DL.getPointerSizeInBits() == 64; 0
1813 ----
1814 PPCTargetStreamer *TS = ----
1815 static_cast(OutStreamer->getTargetStreamer()); 0
1816 ----
1817 emitGNUAttributes(M); 0
1818 ----
1819 if (!TOC.empty()) { 0
1820 const char *Name = isPPC64 ? ".toc" : ".got2"; 0
1821 MCSectionELF *Section = OutContext.getELFSection( 0
1822 Name, ELF::SHT_PROGBITS, ELF::SHF_WRITE | ELF::SHF_ALLOC); ----
1823 OutStreamer->switchSection(Section); 0
1824 if (!isPPC64) 0
1825 OutStreamer->emitValueToAlignment(Align(4)); 0
1826 ----
1827 for (const auto &TOCMapPair : TOC) { 0
1828 const MCSymbol *const TOCEntryTarget = TOCMapPair.first.first; 0
1829 MCSymbol *const TOCEntryLabel = TOCMapPair.second; 0
1830 ----
1831 OutStreamer->emitLabel(TOCEntryLabel); 0
1832 if (isPPC64) 0
1833 TS->emitTCEntry(*TOCEntryTarget, TOCMapPair.first.second); 0
1834 else ----
1835 OutStreamer->emitSymbolValue(TOCEntryTarget, 4); 0
1836 } ----
1837 } ----
1838 ----
1839 PPCAsmPrinter::emitEndOfAsmFile(M); 0
1840 } 0
1841 ----
1842 /// EmitFunctionBodyStart - Emit a global entry point prefix for ELFv2. ----
1843 void PPCLinuxAsmPrinter::emitFunctionBodyStart() { 0
1844 // In the ELFv2 ABI, in functions that use the TOC register, we need to ----
1845 // provide two entry points. The ABI guarantees that when calling the ----
1846 // local entry point, r2 is set up by the caller to contain the TOC base ----
1847 // for this function, and when calling the global entry point, r12 is set ----
1848 // up by the caller to hold the address of the global entry point. We ----
1849 // thus emit a prefix sequence along the following lines: ----
1850 // ----
1851 // func: ----
1852 // .Lfunc_gepNN: ----
1853 // # global entry point ----
1854 // addis r2,r12,(.TOC.-.Lfunc_gepNN)@ha ----
1855 // addi r2,r2,(.TOC.-.Lfunc_gepNN)@l ----
1856 // .Lfunc_lepNN: ----
1857 // .localentry func, .Lfunc_lepNN-.Lfunc_gepNN ----
1858 // # local entry point, followed by function body ----
1859 // ----
1860 // For the Large code model, we create ----
1861 // ----
1862 // .Lfunc_tocNN: ----
1863 // .quad .TOC.-.Lfunc_gepNN # done by EmitFunctionEntryLabel ----
1864 // func: ----
1865 // .Lfunc_gepNN: ----
1866 // # global entry point ----
1867 // ld r2,.Lfunc_tocNN-.Lfunc_gepNN(r12) ----
1868 // add r2,r2,r12 ----
1869 // .Lfunc_lepNN: ----
1870 // .localentry func, .Lfunc_lepNN-.Lfunc_gepNN ----
1871 // # local entry point, followed by function body ----
1872 // ----
1873 // This ensures we have r2 set up correctly while executing the function ----
1874 // body, no matter which entry point is called. ----
1875 const PPCFunctionInfo *PPCFI = MF->getInfo(); 0
1876 const bool UsesX2OrR2 = !MF->getRegInfo().use_empty(PPC::X2) || 0
1877 !MF->getRegInfo().use_empty(PPC::R2); 0
1878 const bool PCrelGEPRequired = Subtarget->isUsingPCRelativeCalls() && 0
1879 UsesX2OrR2 && PPCFI->usesTOCBasePtr(); 0
1880 const bool NonPCrelGEPRequired = !Subtarget->isUsingPCRelativeCalls() && 0
1881 Subtarget->isELFv2ABI() && UsesX2OrR2; 0
1882 ----
1883 // Only do all that if the function uses R2 as the TOC pointer ----
1884 // in the first place. We don't need the global entry point if the ----
1885 // function uses R2 as an allocatable register. ----
1886 if (NonPCrelGEPRequired || PCrelGEPRequired) { 0
1887 // Note: The logic here must be synchronized with the code in the ----
1888 // branch-selection pass which sets the offset of the first block in the ----
1889 // function. This matters because it affects the alignment. ----
1890 MCSymbol *GlobalEntryLabel = PPCFI->getGlobalEPSymbol(*MF); 0
1891 OutStreamer->emitLabel(GlobalEntryLabel); 0
1892 const MCSymbolRefExpr *GlobalEntryLabelExp = ----
1893 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(GlobalEntryLabel, OutContext); 0
1894 ----
1895 if (TM.getCodeModel() != CodeModel::Large) { 0
1896 MCSymbol *TOCSymbol = OutContext.getOrCreateSymbol(StringRef(".TOC.")); 0
1897 const MCExpr *TOCDeltaExpr = ----
1898 MCBinaryExpr::createSub(MCSymbolRefExpr::create(TOCSymbol, OutContext), 0
1899 GlobalEntryLabelExp, OutContext); ----
1900 ----
1901 const MCExpr *TOCDeltaHi = PPCMCExpr::createHa(TOCDeltaExpr, OutContext); 0
1902 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(PPC::ADDIS) 0
1903 .addReg(PPC::X2) 0
1904 .addReg(PPC::X12) 0
1905 .addExpr(TOCDeltaHi)); 0
1906 ----
1907 const MCExpr *TOCDeltaLo = PPCMCExpr::createLo(TOCDeltaExpr, OutContext); 0
1908 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(PPC::ADDI) 0
1909 .addReg(PPC::X2) 0
1910 .addReg(PPC::X2) 0
1911 .addExpr(TOCDeltaLo)); 0
1912 } else { ----
1913 MCSymbol *TOCOffset = PPCFI->getTOCOffsetSymbol(*MF); 0
1914 const MCExpr *TOCOffsetDeltaExpr = ----
1915 MCBinaryExpr::createSub(MCSymbolRefExpr::create(TOCOffset, OutContext), 0
1916 GlobalEntryLabelExp, OutContext); ----
1917 ----
1918 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(PPC::LD) 0
1919 .addReg(PPC::X2) 0
1920 .addExpr(TOCOffsetDeltaExpr) 0
1921 .addReg(PPC::X12)); 0
1922 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(PPC::ADD8) 0
1923 .addReg(PPC::X2) 0
1924 .addReg(PPC::X2) 0
1925 .addReg(PPC::X12)); 0
1926 } ----
1927 ----
1928 MCSymbol *LocalEntryLabel = PPCFI->getLocalEPSymbol(*MF); 0
1929 OutStreamer->emitLabel(LocalEntryLabel); 0
1930 const MCSymbolRefExpr *LocalEntryLabelExp = ----
1931 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(LocalEntryLabel, OutContext); 0
1932 const MCExpr *LocalOffsetExp = ----
1933 MCBinaryExpr::createSub(LocalEntryLabelExp, 0
1934 GlobalEntryLabelExp, OutContext); ----
1935 ----
1936 PPCTargetStreamer *TS = ----
1937 static_cast(OutStreamer->getTargetStreamer()); 0
1938 TS->emitLocalEntry(cast(CurrentFnSym), LocalOffsetExp); 0
1939 } else if (Subtarget->isUsingPCRelativeCalls()) { 0
1940 // When generating the entry point for a function we have a few scenarios ----
1941 // based on whether or not that function uses R2 and whether or not that ----
1942 // function makes calls (or is a leaf function). ----
1943 // 1) A leaf function that does not use R2 (or treats it as callee-saved ----
1944 // and preserves it). In this case st_other=0 and both ----
1945 // the local and global entry points for the function are the same. ----
1946 // No special entry point code is required. ----
1947 // 2) A function uses the TOC pointer R2. This function may or may not have ----
1948 // calls. In this case st_other=[2,6] and the global and local entry ----
1949 // points are different. Code to correctly setup the TOC pointer in R2 ----
1950 // is put between the global and local entry points. This case is ----
1951 // covered by the if statatement above. ----
1952 // 3) A function does not use the TOC pointer R2 but does have calls. ----
1953 // In this case st_other=1 since we do not know whether or not any ----
1954 // of the callees clobber R2. This case is dealt with in this else if ----
1955 // block. Tail calls are considered calls and the st_other should also ----
1956 // be set to 1 in that case as well. ----
1957 // 4) The function does not use the TOC pointer but R2 is used inside ----
1958 // the function. In this case st_other=1 once again. ----
1959 // 5) This function uses inline asm. We mark R2 as reserved if the function ----
1960 // has inline asm as we have to assume that it may be used. ----
1961 if (MF->getFrameInfo().hasCalls() || MF->getFrameInfo().hasTailCall() || 0
1962 MF->hasInlineAsm() || (!PPCFI->usesTOCBasePtr() && UsesX2OrR2)) { 0
1963 PPCTargetStreamer *TS = ----
1964 static_cast(OutStreamer->getTargetStreamer()); 0
1965 TS->emitLocalEntry(cast(CurrentFnSym), 0
1966 MCConstantExpr::create(1, OutContext)); 0
1967 } ----
1968 } ----
1969 } 0
1970 ----
1971 /// EmitFunctionBodyEnd - Print the traceback table before the .size ----
1972 /// directive. ----
1973 /// ----
1974 void PPCLinuxAsmPrinter::emitFunctionBodyEnd() { 0
1975 // Only the 64-bit target requires a traceback table. For now, ----
1976 // we only emit the word of zeroes that GDB requires to find ----
1977 // the end of the function, and zeroes for the eight-byte ----
1978 // mandatory fields. ----
1979 // FIXME: We should fill in the eight-byte mandatory fields as described in ----
1980 // the PPC64 ELF ABI (this is a low-priority item because GDB does not ----
1981 // currently make use of these fields). ----
1982 if (Subtarget->isPPC64()) { 0
1983 OutStreamer->emitIntValue(0, 4/*size*/); 0
1984 OutStreamer->emitIntValue(0, 8/*size*/); 0
1985 } ----
1986 } 0
1987 ----
1988 void PPCAIXAsmPrinter::emitLinkage(const GlobalValue *GV, 0
1989 MCSymbol *GVSym) const { ----
1990 ----
1991 assert(MAI->hasVisibilityOnlyWithLinkage() && 0
1992 "AIX's linkage directives take a visibility setting."); ----
1993 ----
1994 MCSymbolAttr LinkageAttr = MCSA_Invalid; 0
1995 switch (GV->getLinkage()) { 0
1996 case GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage: 0
1997 LinkageAttr = GV->isDeclaration() ? MCSA_Extern : MCSA_Global; 0
1998 break; 0
1999 case GlobalValue::LinkOnceAnyLinkage: 0
2000 case GlobalValue::LinkOnceODRLinkage: ----
2001 case GlobalValue::WeakAnyLinkage: ----
2002 case GlobalValue::WeakODRLinkage: ----
2003 case GlobalValue::ExternalWeakLinkage: ----
2004 LinkageAttr = MCSA_Weak; 0
2005 break; 0
2006 case GlobalValue::AvailableExternallyLinkage: 0
2007 LinkageAttr = MCSA_Extern; 0
2008 break; 0
2009 case GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage: 0
2010 return; 0
2011 case GlobalValue::InternalLinkage: 0
2012 assert(GV->getVisibility() == GlobalValue::DefaultVisibility && 0
2013 "InternalLinkage should not have other visibility setting."); ----
2014 LinkageAttr = MCSA_LGlobal; 0
2015 break; 0
2016 case GlobalValue::AppendingLinkage: 0
2017 llvm_unreachable("Should never emit this"); 0
2018 case GlobalValue::CommonLinkage: 0
2019 llvm_unreachable("CommonLinkage of XCOFF should not come to this path"); 0
2020 } ----
2021 ----
2022 assert(LinkageAttr != MCSA_Invalid && "LinkageAttr should not MCSA_Invalid."); 0
2023 ----
2024 MCSymbolAttr VisibilityAttr = MCSA_Invalid; 0
2025 if (!TM.getIgnoreXCOFFVisibility()) { 0
2026 if (GV->hasDLLExportStorageClass() && !GV->hasDefaultVisibility()) 0
2027 report_fatal_error( 0
2028 "Cannot not be both dllexport and non-default visibility"); ----
2029 switch (GV->getVisibility()) { 0
2030 ----
2031 // TODO: "internal" Visibility needs to go here. ----
2032 case GlobalValue::DefaultVisibility: 0
2033 if (GV->hasDLLExportStorageClass()) 0
2034 VisibilityAttr = MAI->getExportedVisibilityAttr(); 0
2035 break; 0
2036 case GlobalValue::HiddenVisibility: 0
2037 VisibilityAttr = MAI->getHiddenVisibilityAttr(); 0
2038 break; 0
2039 case GlobalValue::ProtectedVisibility: 0
2040 VisibilityAttr = MAI->getProtectedVisibilityAttr(); 0
2041 break; 0
2042 } ----
2043 } ----
2044 ----
2045 OutStreamer->emitXCOFFSymbolLinkageWithVisibility(GVSym, LinkageAttr, 0
2046 VisibilityAttr); ----
2047 } ----
2048 ----
2049 void PPCAIXAsmPrinter::SetupMachineFunction(MachineFunction &MF) { 0
2050 // Setup CurrentFnDescSym and its containing csect. ----
2051 MCSectionXCOFF *FnDescSec = ----
2052 cast(getObjFileLowering().getSectionForFunctionDescriptor( 0
2053 &MF.getFunction(), TM)); 0
2054 FnDescSec->setAlignment(Align(Subtarget->isPPC64() ? 8 : 4)); 0
2055 ----
2056 CurrentFnDescSym = FnDescSec->getQualNameSymbol(); 0
2057 ----
2058 return AsmPrinter::SetupMachineFunction(MF); 0
2059 } ----
2060 ----
2061 uint16_t PPCAIXAsmPrinter::getNumberOfVRSaved() { 0
2062 // Calculate the number of VRs be saved. ----
2063 // Vector registers 20 through 31 are marked as reserved and cannot be used ----
2064 // in the default ABI. ----
2065 const PPCSubtarget &Subtarget = MF->getSubtarget(); 0
2066 if (Subtarget.isAIXABI() && Subtarget.hasAltivec() && 0
2067 TM.getAIXExtendedAltivecABI()) { 0
2068 const MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MF->getRegInfo(); 0
2069 for (unsigned Reg = PPC::V20; Reg <= PPC::V31; ++Reg) 0
2070 if (MRI.isPhysRegModified(Reg)) 0
2071 // Number of VRs saved. ----
2072 return PPC::V31 - Reg + 1; 0
2073 } ----
2074 return 0; 0
2075 } ----
2076 ----
2077 void PPCAIXAsmPrinter::emitFunctionBodyEnd() { 0
2078 ----
2079 if (!TM.getXCOFFTracebackTable()) 0
2080 return; 0
2081 ----
2082 emitTracebackTable(); 0
2083 ----
2084 // If ShouldEmitEHBlock returns true, then the eh info table ----
2085 // will be emitted via `AIXException::endFunction`. Otherwise, we ----
2086 // need to emit a dumy eh info table when VRs are saved. We could not ----
2087 // consolidate these two places into one because there is no easy way ----
2088 // to access register information in `AIXException` class. ----
2089 if (!TargetLoweringObjectFileXCOFF::ShouldEmitEHBlock(MF) && 0
2090 (getNumberOfVRSaved() > 0)) { 0
2091 // Emit dummy EH Info Table. ----
2092 OutStreamer->switchSection(getObjFileLowering().getCompactUnwindSection()); 0
2093 MCSymbol *EHInfoLabel = ----
2094 TargetLoweringObjectFileXCOFF::getEHInfoTableSymbol(MF); 0
2095 OutStreamer->emitLabel(EHInfoLabel); 0
2096 ----
2097 // Version number. ----
2098 OutStreamer->emitInt32(0); 0
2099 ----
2100 const DataLayout &DL = MMI->getModule()->getDataLayout(); 0
2101 const unsigned PointerSize = DL.getPointerSize(); 0
2102 // Add necessary paddings in 64 bit mode. ----
2103 OutStreamer->emitValueToAlignment(Align(PointerSize)); 0
2104 ----
2105 OutStreamer->emitIntValue(0, PointerSize); 0
2106 OutStreamer->emitIntValue(0, PointerSize); 0
2107 OutStreamer->switchSection(MF->getSection()); 0
2108 } ----
2109 } ----
2110 ----
2111 void PPCAIXAsmPrinter::emitTracebackTable() { 0
2112 ----
2113 // Create a symbol for the end of function. ----
2114 MCSymbol *FuncEnd = createTempSymbol(MF->getName()); 0
2115 OutStreamer->emitLabel(FuncEnd); 0
2116 ----
2117 OutStreamer->AddComment("Traceback table begin"); 0
2118 // Begin with a fullword of zero. ----
2119 OutStreamer->emitIntValueInHexWithPadding(0, 4 /*size*/); 0
2120 ----
2121 SmallString<128> CommentString; 0
2122 raw_svector_ostream CommentOS(CommentString); 0
2123 ----
2124 auto EmitComment = [&]() { 0
2125 OutStreamer->AddComment(CommentOS.str()); 0
2126 CommentString.clear(); 0
2127 }; 0
2128 ----
2129 auto EmitCommentAndValue = [&](uint64_t Value, int Size) { 0
2130 EmitComment(); 0
2131 OutStreamer->emitIntValueInHexWithPadding(Value, Size); 0
2132 }; 0
2133 ----
2134 unsigned int Version = 0; 0
2135 CommentOS << "Version = " << Version; 0
2136 EmitCommentAndValue(Version, 1); 0
2137 ----
2138 // There is a lack of information in the IR to assist with determining the ----
2139 // source language. AIX exception handling mechanism would only search for ----
2140 // personality routine and LSDA area when such language supports exception ----
2141 // handling. So to be conservatively correct and allow runtime to do its job, ----
2142 // we need to set it to C++ for now. ----
2143 TracebackTable::LanguageID LanguageIdentifier = 0
2144 TracebackTable::CPlusPlus; // C++ ----
2145 ----
2146 CommentOS << "Language = " 0
2147 << getNameForTracebackTableLanguageId(LanguageIdentifier); 0
2148 EmitCommentAndValue(LanguageIdentifier, 1); 0
2149 ----
2150 // This is only populated for the third and fourth bytes. ----
2151 uint32_t FirstHalfOfMandatoryField = 0; 0
2152 ----
2153 // Emit the 3rd byte of the mandatory field. ----
2154 ----
2155 // We always set traceback offset bit to true. ----
2156 FirstHalfOfMandatoryField |= TracebackTable::HasTraceBackTableOffsetMask; 0
2157 ----
2158 const PPCFunctionInfo *FI = MF->getInfo(); 0
2159 const MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MF->getRegInfo(); 0
2160 ----
2161 // Check the function uses floating-point processor instructions or not ----
2162 for (unsigned Reg = PPC::F0; Reg <= PPC::F31; ++Reg) { 0
2163 if (MRI.isPhysRegUsed(Reg, /* SkipRegMaskTest */ true)) { 0
2164 FirstHalfOfMandatoryField |= TracebackTable::IsFloatingPointPresentMask; 0
2165 break; 0
2166 } ----
2167 } ----
2168 ----
2169 #define GENBOOLCOMMENT(Prefix, V, Field) \ ----
2170 CommentOS << (Prefix) << ((V) & (TracebackTable::Field##Mask) ? "+" : "-") \ ----
2171 << #Field ----
2172 ----
2173 #define GENVALUECOMMENT(PrefixAndName, V, Field) \ ----
2174 CommentOS << (PrefixAndName) << " = " \ ----
2175 << static_cast(((V) & (TracebackTable::Field##Mask)) >> \ ----
2176 (TracebackTable::Field##Shift)) ----
2177 ----
2178 GENBOOLCOMMENT("", FirstHalfOfMandatoryField, IsGlobaLinkage); 0
2179 GENBOOLCOMMENT(", ", FirstHalfOfMandatoryField, IsOutOfLineEpilogOrPrologue); 0
2180 EmitComment(); 0
2181 ----
2182 GENBOOLCOMMENT("", FirstHalfOfMandatoryField, HasTraceBackTableOffset); 0
2183 GENBOOLCOMMENT(", ", FirstHalfOfMandatoryField, IsInternalProcedure); 0
2184 EmitComment(); 0
2185 ----
2186 GENBOOLCOMMENT("", FirstHalfOfMandatoryField, HasControlledStorage); 0
2187 GENBOOLCOMMENT(", ", FirstHalfOfMandatoryField, IsTOCless); 0
2188 EmitComment(); 0
2189 ----
2190 GENBOOLCOMMENT("", FirstHalfOfMandatoryField, IsFloatingPointPresent); 0
2191 EmitComment(); 0
2192 GENBOOLCOMMENT("", FirstHalfOfMandatoryField, 0
2193 IsFloatingPointOperationLogOrAbortEnabled); ----
2194 EmitComment(); 0
2195 ----
2196 OutStreamer->emitIntValueInHexWithPadding( 0
2197 (FirstHalfOfMandatoryField & 0x0000ff00) >> 8, 1); 0
2198 ----
2199 // Set the 4th byte of the mandatory field. ----
2200 FirstHalfOfMandatoryField |= TracebackTable::IsFunctionNamePresentMask; 0
2201 ----
2202 const PPCRegisterInfo *RegInfo = ----
2203 static_cast(Subtarget->getRegisterInfo()); 0
2204 Register FrameReg = RegInfo->getFrameRegister(*MF); 0
2205 if (FrameReg == (Subtarget->isPPC64() ? PPC::X31 : PPC::R31)) 0
2206 FirstHalfOfMandatoryField |= TracebackTable::IsAllocaUsedMask; 0
2207 ----
2208 const SmallVectorImpl &MustSaveCRs = FI->getMustSaveCRs(); 0
2209 if (!MustSaveCRs.empty()) 0
2210 FirstHalfOfMandatoryField |= TracebackTable::IsCRSavedMask; 0
2211 ----
2212 if (FI->mustSaveLR()) 0
2213 FirstHalfOfMandatoryField |= TracebackTable::IsLRSavedMask; 0
2214 ----
2215 GENBOOLCOMMENT("", FirstHalfOfMandatoryField, IsInterruptHandler); 0
2216 GENBOOLCOMMENT(", ", FirstHalfOfMandatoryField, IsFunctionNamePresent); 0
2217 GENBOOLCOMMENT(", ", FirstHalfOfMandatoryField, IsAllocaUsed); 0
2218 EmitComment(); 0
2219 GENVALUECOMMENT("OnConditionDirective", FirstHalfOfMandatoryField, 0
2220 OnConditionDirective); ----
2221 GENBOOLCOMMENT(", ", FirstHalfOfMandatoryField, IsCRSaved); 0
2222 GENBOOLCOMMENT(", ", FirstHalfOfMandatoryField, IsLRSaved); 0
2223 EmitComment(); 0
2224 OutStreamer->emitIntValueInHexWithPadding((FirstHalfOfMandatoryField & 0xff), 0
2225 1); ----
2226 ----
2227 // Set the 5th byte of mandatory field. ----
2228 uint32_t SecondHalfOfMandatoryField = 0; 0
2229 ----
2230 SecondHalfOfMandatoryField |= MF->getFrameInfo().getStackSize() 0
2231 ? TracebackTable::IsBackChainStoredMask 0
2232 : 0; ----
2233 ----
2234 uint32_t FPRSaved = 0; 0
2235 for (unsigned Reg = PPC::F14; Reg <= PPC::F31; ++Reg) { 0
2236 if (MRI.isPhysRegModified(Reg)) { 0
2237 FPRSaved = PPC::F31 - Reg + 1; 0
2238 break; 0
2239 } ----
2240 } ----
2241 SecondHalfOfMandatoryField |= (FPRSaved << TracebackTable::FPRSavedShift) & 0
2242 TracebackTable::FPRSavedMask; ----
2243 GENBOOLCOMMENT("", SecondHalfOfMandatoryField, IsBackChainStored); 0
2244 GENBOOLCOMMENT(", ", SecondHalfOfMandatoryField, IsFixup); 0
2245 GENVALUECOMMENT(", NumOfFPRsSaved", SecondHalfOfMandatoryField, FPRSaved); 0
2246 EmitComment(); 0
2247 OutStreamer->emitIntValueInHexWithPadding( 0
2248 (SecondHalfOfMandatoryField & 0xff000000) >> 24, 1); 0
2249 ----
2250 // Set the 6th byte of mandatory field. ----
2251 ----
2252 // Check whether has Vector Instruction,We only treat instructions uses vector ----
2253 // register as vector instructions. ----
2254 bool HasVectorInst = false; 0
2255 for (unsigned Reg = PPC::V0; Reg <= PPC::V31; ++Reg) 0
2256 if (MRI.isPhysRegUsed(Reg, /* SkipRegMaskTest */ true)) { 0
2257 // Has VMX instruction. ----
2258 HasVectorInst = true; 0
2259 break; 0
2260 } ----
2261 ----
2262 if (FI->hasVectorParms() || HasVectorInst) 0
2263 SecondHalfOfMandatoryField |= TracebackTable::HasVectorInfoMask; 0
2264 ----
2265 uint16_t NumOfVRSaved = getNumberOfVRSaved(); 0
2266 bool ShouldEmitEHBlock = ----
2267 TargetLoweringObjectFileXCOFF::ShouldEmitEHBlock(MF) || NumOfVRSaved > 0; 0
2268 ----
2269 if (ShouldEmitEHBlock) 0
2270 SecondHalfOfMandatoryField |= TracebackTable::HasExtensionTableMask; 0
2271 ----
2272 uint32_t GPRSaved = 0; 0
2273 ----
2274 // X13 is reserved under 64-bit environment. ----
2275 unsigned GPRBegin = Subtarget->isPPC64() ? PPC::X14 : PPC::R13; 0
2276 unsigned GPREnd = Subtarget->isPPC64() ? PPC::X31 : PPC::R31; 0
2277 ----
2278 for (unsigned Reg = GPRBegin; Reg <= GPREnd; ++Reg) { 0
2279 if (MRI.isPhysRegModified(Reg)) { 0
2280 GPRSaved = GPREnd - Reg + 1; 0
2281 break; 0
2282 } ----
2283 } ----
2284 ----
2285 SecondHalfOfMandatoryField |= (GPRSaved << TracebackTable::GPRSavedShift) & 0
2286 TracebackTable::GPRSavedMask; ----
2287 ----
2288 GENBOOLCOMMENT("", SecondHalfOfMandatoryField, HasExtensionTable); 0
2289 GENBOOLCOMMENT(", ", SecondHalfOfMandatoryField, HasVectorInfo); 0
2290 GENVALUECOMMENT(", NumOfGPRsSaved", SecondHalfOfMandatoryField, GPRSaved); 0
2291 EmitComment(); 0
2292 OutStreamer->emitIntValueInHexWithPadding( 0
2293 (SecondHalfOfMandatoryField & 0x00ff0000) >> 16, 1); 0
2294 ----
2295 // Set the 7th byte of mandatory field. ----
2296 uint32_t NumberOfFixedParms = FI->getFixedParmsNum(); 0
2297 SecondHalfOfMandatoryField |= 0
2298 (NumberOfFixedParms << TracebackTable::NumberOfFixedParmsShift) & 0
2299 TracebackTable::NumberOfFixedParmsMask; ----
2300 GENVALUECOMMENT("NumberOfFixedParms", SecondHalfOfMandatoryField, 0
2301 NumberOfFixedParms); ----
2302 EmitComment(); 0
2303 OutStreamer->emitIntValueInHexWithPadding( 0
2304 (SecondHalfOfMandatoryField & 0x0000ff00) >> 8, 1); 0
2305 ----
2306 // Set the 8th byte of mandatory field. ----
2307 ----
2308 // Always set parameter on stack. ----
2309 SecondHalfOfMandatoryField |= TracebackTable::HasParmsOnStackMask; 0
2310 ----
2311 uint32_t NumberOfFPParms = FI->getFloatingPointParmsNum(); 0
2312 SecondHalfOfMandatoryField |= 0
2313 (NumberOfFPParms << TracebackTable::NumberOfFloatingPointParmsShift) & 0
2314 TracebackTable::NumberOfFloatingPointParmsMask; ----
2315 ----
2316 GENVALUECOMMENT("NumberOfFPParms", SecondHalfOfMandatoryField, 0
2317 NumberOfFloatingPointParms); ----
2318 GENBOOLCOMMENT(", ", SecondHalfOfMandatoryField, HasParmsOnStack); 0
2319 EmitComment(); 0
2320 OutStreamer->emitIntValueInHexWithPadding(SecondHalfOfMandatoryField & 0xff, 0
2321 1); ----
2322 ----
2323 // Generate the optional fields of traceback table. ----
2324 ----
2325 // Parameter type. ----
2326 if (NumberOfFixedParms || NumberOfFPParms) { 0
2327 uint32_t ParmsTypeValue = FI->getParmsType(); 0
2328 ----
2329 Expected> ParmsType = ----
2330 FI->hasVectorParms() 0
2331 ? XCOFF::parseParmsTypeWithVecInfo( ----
2332 ParmsTypeValue, NumberOfFixedParms, NumberOfFPParms, ----
2333 FI->getVectorParmsNum()) ----
2334 : XCOFF::parseParmsType(ParmsTypeValue, NumberOfFixedParms, ----
2335 NumberOfFPParms); 0
2336 ----
2337 assert(ParmsType && toString(ParmsType.takeError()).c_str()); 0
2338 if (ParmsType) { 0
2339 CommentOS << "Parameter type = " << ParmsType.get(); 0
2340 EmitComment(); 0
2341 } ----
2342 OutStreamer->emitIntValueInHexWithPadding(ParmsTypeValue, 0
2343 sizeof(ParmsTypeValue)); ----
2344 } 0
2345 // Traceback table offset. ----
2346 OutStreamer->AddComment("Function size"); 0
2347 if (FirstHalfOfMandatoryField & TracebackTable::HasTraceBackTableOffsetMask) { 0
2348 MCSymbol *FuncSectSym = getObjFileLowering().getFunctionEntryPointSymbol( 0
2349 &(MF->getFunction()), TM); 0
2350 OutStreamer->emitAbsoluteSymbolDiff(FuncEnd, FuncSectSym, 4); 0
2351 } ----
2352 ----
2353 // Since we unset the Int_Handler. ----
2354 if (FirstHalfOfMandatoryField & TracebackTable::IsInterruptHandlerMask) 0
2355 report_fatal_error("Hand_Mask not implement yet"); 0
2356 ----
2357 if (FirstHalfOfMandatoryField & TracebackTable::HasControlledStorageMask) 0
2358 report_fatal_error("Ctl_Info not implement yet"); 0
2359 ----
2360 if (FirstHalfOfMandatoryField & TracebackTable::IsFunctionNamePresentMask) { 0
2361 StringRef Name = MF->getName().substr(0, INT16_MAX); 0
2362 int16_t NameLength = Name.size(); 0
2363 CommentOS << "Function name len = " 0
2364 << static_cast(NameLength); 0
2365 EmitCommentAndValue(NameLength, 2); 0
2366 OutStreamer->AddComment("Function Name"); 0
2367 OutStreamer->emitBytes(Name); 0
2368 } ----
2369 ----
2370 if (FirstHalfOfMandatoryField & TracebackTable::IsAllocaUsedMask) { 0
2371 uint8_t AllocReg = XCOFF::AllocRegNo; 0
2372 OutStreamer->AddComment("AllocaUsed"); 0
2373 OutStreamer->emitIntValueInHex(AllocReg, sizeof(AllocReg)); 0
2374 } ----
2375 ----
2376 if (SecondHalfOfMandatoryField & TracebackTable::HasVectorInfoMask) { 0
2377 uint16_t VRData = 0; 0
2378 if (NumOfVRSaved) { 0
2379 // Number of VRs saved. ----
2380 VRData |= (NumOfVRSaved << TracebackTable::NumberOfVRSavedShift) & 0
2381 TracebackTable::NumberOfVRSavedMask; ----
2382 // This bit is supposed to set only when the special register ----
2383 // VRSAVE is saved on stack. ----
2384 // However, IBM XL compiler sets the bit when any vector registers ----
2385 // are saved on the stack. We will follow XL's behavior on AIX ----
2386 // so that we don't get surprise behavior change for C code. ----
2387 VRData |= TracebackTable::IsVRSavedOnStackMask; 0
2388 } ----
2389 ----
2390 // Set has_varargs. ----
2391 if (FI->getVarArgsFrameIndex()) 0
2392 VRData |= TracebackTable::HasVarArgsMask; 0
2393 ----
2394 // Vector parameters number. ----
2395 unsigned VectorParmsNum = FI->getVectorParmsNum(); 0
2396 VRData |= (VectorParmsNum << TracebackTable::NumberOfVectorParmsShift) & 0
2397 TracebackTable::NumberOfVectorParmsMask; ----
2398 ----
2399 if (HasVectorInst) 0
2400 VRData |= TracebackTable::HasVMXInstructionMask; 0
2401 ----
2402 GENVALUECOMMENT("NumOfVRsSaved", VRData, NumberOfVRSaved); 0
2403 GENBOOLCOMMENT(", ", VRData, IsVRSavedOnStack); 0
2404 GENBOOLCOMMENT(", ", VRData, HasVarArgs); 0
2405 EmitComment(); 0
2406 OutStreamer->emitIntValueInHexWithPadding((VRData & 0xff00) >> 8, 1); 0
2407 ----
2408 GENVALUECOMMENT("NumOfVectorParams", VRData, NumberOfVectorParms); 0
2409 GENBOOLCOMMENT(", ", VRData, HasVMXInstruction); 0
2410 EmitComment(); 0
2411 OutStreamer->emitIntValueInHexWithPadding(VRData & 0x00ff, 1); 0
2412 ----
2413 uint32_t VecParmTypeValue = FI->getVecExtParmsType(); 0
2414 ----
2415 Expected> VecParmsType = ----
2416 XCOFF::parseVectorParmsType(VecParmTypeValue, VectorParmsNum); 0
2417 assert(VecParmsType && toString(VecParmsType.takeError()).c_str()); 0
2418 if (VecParmsType) { 0
2419 CommentOS << "Vector Parameter type = " << VecParmsType.get(); 0
2420 EmitComment(); 0
2421 } ----
2422 OutStreamer->emitIntValueInHexWithPadding(VecParmTypeValue, 0
2423 sizeof(VecParmTypeValue)); ----
2424 // Padding 2 bytes. ----
2425 CommentOS << "Padding"; 0
2426 EmitCommentAndValue(0, 2); 0
2427 } 0
2428 ----
2429 uint8_t ExtensionTableFlag = 0; 0
2430 if (SecondHalfOfMandatoryField & TracebackTable::HasExtensionTableMask) { 0
2431 if (ShouldEmitEHBlock) 0
2432 ExtensionTableFlag |= ExtendedTBTableFlag::TB_EH_INFO; 0
2433 if (EnableSSPCanaryBitInTB && 0
2434 TargetLoweringObjectFileXCOFF::ShouldSetSSPCanaryBitInTB(MF)) 0
2435 ExtensionTableFlag |= ExtendedTBTableFlag::TB_SSP_CANARY; 0
2436 ----
2437 CommentOS << "ExtensionTableFlag = " 0
2438 << getExtendedTBTableFlagString(ExtensionTableFlag); 0
2439 EmitCommentAndValue(ExtensionTableFlag, sizeof(ExtensionTableFlag)); 0
2440 } ----
2441 ----
2442 if (ExtensionTableFlag & ExtendedTBTableFlag::TB_EH_INFO) { 0
2443 auto &Ctx = OutStreamer->getContext(); 0
2444 MCSymbol *EHInfoSym = ----
2445 TargetLoweringObjectFileXCOFF::getEHInfoTableSymbol(MF); 0
2446 MCSymbol *TOCEntry = lookUpOrCreateTOCEntry(EHInfoSym, TOCType_EHBlock); 0
2447 const MCSymbol *TOCBaseSym = ----
2448 cast(getObjFileLowering().getTOCBaseSection()) 0
2449 ->getQualNameSymbol(); 0
2450 const MCExpr *Exp = ----
2451 MCBinaryExpr::createSub(MCSymbolRefExpr::create(TOCEntry, Ctx), 0
2452 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(TOCBaseSym, Ctx), Ctx); 0
2453 ----
2454 const DataLayout &DL = getDataLayout(); 0
2455 OutStreamer->emitValueToAlignment(Align(4)); 0
2456 OutStreamer->AddComment("EHInfo Table"); 0
2457 OutStreamer->emitValue(Exp, DL.getPointerSize()); 0
2458 } ----
2459 #undef GENBOOLCOMMENT ----
2460 #undef GENVALUECOMMENT ----
2461 } 0
2462 ----
2463 static bool isSpecialLLVMGlobalArrayToSkip(const GlobalVariable *GV) { 0
2464 return GV->hasAppendingLinkage() && 0
2465 StringSwitch(GV->getName()) 0
2466 // TODO: Linker could still eliminate the GV if we just skip ----
2467 // handling llvm.used array. Skipping them for now until we or the ----
2468 // AIX OS team come up with a good solution. ----
2469 .Case("llvm.used", true) 0
2470 // It's correct to just skip llvm.compiler.used array here. ----
2471 .Case("llvm.compiler.used", true) 0
2472 .Default(false); 0
2473 } ----
2474 ----
2475 static bool isSpecialLLVMGlobalArrayForStaticInit(const GlobalVariable *GV) { 0
2476 return StringSwitch(GV->getName()) 0
2477 .Cases("llvm.global_ctors", "llvm.global_dtors", true) 0
2478 .Default(false); 0
2479 } ----
2480 ----
2481 uint64_t PPCAIXAsmPrinter::getAliasOffset(const Constant *C) { 0
2482 if (auto *GA = dyn_cast(C)) 0
2483 return getAliasOffset(GA->getAliasee()); 0
2484 if (auto *CE = dyn_cast(C)) { 0
2485 const MCExpr *LowC = lowerConstant(CE); 0
2486 const MCBinaryExpr *CBE = dyn_cast(LowC); 0
2487 if (!CBE) 0
2488 return 0; 0
2489 if (CBE->getOpcode() != MCBinaryExpr::Add) 0
2490 report_fatal_error("Only adding an offset is supported now."); 0
2491 auto *RHS = dyn_cast(CBE->getRHS()); 0
2492 if (!RHS) 0
2493 report_fatal_error("Unable to get the offset of alias."); 0
2494 return RHS->getValue(); 0
2495 } ----
2496 return 0; 0
2497 } ----
2498 ----
2499 void PPCAIXAsmPrinter::emitGlobalVariable(const GlobalVariable *GV) { 0
2500 // Special LLVM global arrays have been handled at the initialization. ----
2501 if (isSpecialLLVMGlobalArrayToSkip(GV) || isSpecialLLVMGlobalArrayForStaticInit(GV)) 0
2502 return; 0
2503 ----
2504 // If the Global Variable has the toc-data attribute, it needs to be emitted ----
2505 // when we emit the .toc section. ----
2506 if (GV->hasAttribute("toc-data")) { 0
2507 TOCDataGlobalVars.push_back(GV); 0
2508 return; 0
2509 } ----
2510 ----
2511 emitGlobalVariableHelper(GV); 0
2512 } ----
2513 ----
2514 void PPCAIXAsmPrinter::emitGlobalVariableHelper(const GlobalVariable *GV) { 0
2515 assert(!GV->getName().startswith("llvm.") && 0
2516 "Unhandled intrinsic global variable."); ----
2517 ----
2518 if (GV->hasComdat()) 0
2519 report_fatal_error("COMDAT not yet supported by AIX."); 0
2520 ----
2521 MCSymbolXCOFF *GVSym = cast(getSymbol(GV)); 0
2522 ----
2523 if (GV->isDeclarationForLinker()) { 0
2524 emitLinkage(GV, GVSym); 0
2525 return; 0
2526 } ----
2527 ----
2528 SectionKind GVKind = getObjFileLowering().getKindForGlobal(GV, TM); 0
2529 if (!GVKind.isGlobalWriteableData() && !GVKind.isReadOnly() && 0
2530 !GVKind.isThreadLocal()) // Checks for both ThreadData and ThreadBSS. 0
2531 report_fatal_error("Encountered a global variable kind that is " 0
2532 "not supported yet."); ----
2533 ----
2534 // Print GV in verbose mode ----
2535 if (isVerbose()) { 0
2536 if (GV->hasInitializer()) { 0
2537 GV->printAsOperand(OutStreamer->getCommentOS(), 0
2538 /*PrintType=*/false, GV->getParent()); ----
2539 OutStreamer->getCommentOS() << '\n'; 0
2540 } ----
2541 } ----
2542 ----
2543 MCSectionXCOFF *Csect = cast( 0
2544 getObjFileLowering().SectionForGlobal(GV, GVKind, TM)); 0
2545 ----
2546 // Switch to the containing csect. ----
2547 OutStreamer->switchSection(Csect); 0
2548 ----
2549 const DataLayout &DL = GV->getParent()->getDataLayout(); 0
2550 ----
2551 // Handle common and zero-initialized local symbols. ----
2552 if (GV->hasCommonLinkage() || GVKind.isBSSLocal() || 0
2553 GVKind.isThreadBSSLocal()) { 0
2554 Align Alignment = GV->getAlign().value_or(DL.getPreferredAlign(GV)); 0
2555 uint64_t Size = DL.getTypeAllocSize(GV->getValueType()); 0
2556 GVSym->setStorageClass( 0
2557 TargetLoweringObjectFileXCOFF::getStorageClassForGlobal(GV)); 0
2558 ----
2559 if (GVKind.isBSSLocal() || GVKind.isThreadBSSLocal()) 0
2560 OutStreamer->emitXCOFFLocalCommonSymbol( 0
2561 OutContext.getOrCreateSymbol(GVSym->getSymbolTableName()), Size, 0
2562 GVSym, Alignment); ----
2563 else ----
2564 OutStreamer->emitCommonSymbol(GVSym, Size, Alignment); 0
2565 return; 0
2566 } ----
2567 ----
2568 MCSymbol *EmittedInitSym = GVSym; 0
2569 ----
2570 // Emit linkage for the global variable and its aliases. ----
2571 emitLinkage(GV, EmittedInitSym); 0
2572 for (const GlobalAlias *GA : GOAliasMap[GV]) 0
2573 emitLinkage(GA, getSymbol(GA)); 0
2574 ----
2575 emitAlignment(getGVAlignment(GV, DL), GV); 0
2576 ----
2577 // When -fdata-sections is enabled, every GlobalVariable will ----
2578 // be put into its own csect; therefore, label is not necessary here. ----
2579 if (!TM.getDataSections() || GV->hasSection()) 0
2580 OutStreamer->emitLabel(EmittedInitSym); 0
2581 ----
2582 // No alias to emit. ----
2583 if (!GOAliasMap[GV].size()) { 0
2584 emitGlobalConstant(GV->getParent()->getDataLayout(), GV->getInitializer()); 0
2585 return; 0
2586 } ----
2587 ----
2588 // Aliases with the same offset should be aligned. Record the list of aliases ----
2589 // associated with the offset. ----
2590 AliasMapTy AliasList; 0
2591 for (const GlobalAlias *GA : GOAliasMap[GV]) 0
2592 AliasList[getAliasOffset(GA->getAliasee())].push_back(GA); 0
2593 ----
2594 // Emit alias label and element value for global variable. ----
2595 emitGlobalConstant(GV->getParent()->getDataLayout(), GV->getInitializer(), 0
2596 &AliasList); ----
2597 } 0
2598 ----
2599 void PPCAIXAsmPrinter::emitFunctionDescriptor() { 0
2600 const DataLayout &DL = getDataLayout(); 0
2601 const unsigned PointerSize = DL.getPointerSizeInBits() == 64 ? 8 : 4; 0
2602 ----
2603 MCSectionSubPair Current = OutStreamer->getCurrentSection(); 0
2604 // Emit function descriptor. ----
2605 OutStreamer->switchSection( 0
2606 cast(CurrentFnDescSym)->getRepresentedCsect()); 0
2607 ----
2608 // Emit aliasing label for function descriptor csect. ----
2609 for (const GlobalAlias *Alias : GOAliasMap[&MF->getFunction()]) 0
2610 OutStreamer->emitLabel(getSymbol(Alias)); 0
2611 ----
2612 // Emit function entry point address. ----
2613 OutStreamer->emitValue(MCSymbolRefExpr::create(CurrentFnSym, OutContext), 0
2614 PointerSize); ----
2615 // Emit TOC base address. ----
2616 const MCSymbol *TOCBaseSym = ----
2617 cast(getObjFileLowering().getTOCBaseSection()) 0
2618 ->getQualNameSymbol(); 0
2619 OutStreamer->emitValue(MCSymbolRefExpr::create(TOCBaseSym, OutContext), 0
2620 PointerSize); ----
2621 // Emit a null environment pointer. ----
2622 OutStreamer->emitIntValue(0, PointerSize); 0
2623 ----
2624 OutStreamer->switchSection(Current.first, Current.second); 0
2625 } 0
2626 ----
2627 void PPCAIXAsmPrinter::emitFunctionEntryLabel() { 0
2628 // It's not necessary to emit the label when we have individual ----
2629 // function in its own csect. ----
2630 if (!TM.getFunctionSections()) 0
2631 PPCAsmPrinter::emitFunctionEntryLabel(); 0
2632 ----
2633 // Emit aliasing label for function entry point label. ----
2634 for (const GlobalAlias *Alias : GOAliasMap[&MF->getFunction()]) 0
2635 OutStreamer->emitLabel( 0
2636 getObjFileLowering().getFunctionEntryPointSymbol(Alias, TM)); 0
2637 } 0
2638 ----
2639 void PPCAIXAsmPrinter::emitPGORefs() { 0
2640 if (OutContext.hasXCOFFSection( 0
2641 "__llvm_prf_cnts", ----
2642 XCOFF::CsectProperties(XCOFF::XMC_RW, XCOFF::XTY_SD))) { ----
2643 MCSection *CntsSection = OutContext.getXCOFFSection( 0
2644 "__llvm_prf_cnts", SectionKind::getData(), ----
2645 XCOFF::CsectProperties(XCOFF::XMC_RW, XCOFF::XTY_SD), 0
2646 /*MultiSymbolsAllowed*/ true); ----
2647 ----
2648 OutStreamer->switchSection(CntsSection); 0
2649 if (OutContext.hasXCOFFSection( 0

2711 bool PPCAIXAsmPrinter::doInitialization(Module &M) { 0
2712 const bool Result = PPCAsmPrinter::doInitialization(M); 0
2713 ----
2714 auto setCsectAlignment = [this](const GlobalObject *GO) { 0
2715 // Declarations have 0 alignment which is set by default. ----
2716 if (GO->isDeclarationForLinker()) 0
2717 return; 0
2718 ----
2719 SectionKind GOKind = getObjFileLowering().getKindForGlobal(GO, TM); 0
2720 MCSectionXCOFF *Csect = cast( 0
2721 getObjFileLowering().SectionForGlobal(GO, GOKind, TM)); 0
2722 ----
2723 Align GOAlign = getGVAlignment(GO, GO->getParent()->getDataLayout()); 0
2724 Csect->ensureMinAlignment(GOAlign); 0
2725 }; 0
2726 ----
2727 // We need to know, up front, the alignment of csects for the assembly path, ----
2728 // because once a .csect directive gets emitted, we could not change the ----
2729 // alignment value on it. ----
2730 for (const auto &G : M.globals()) { 0
2731 if (isSpecialLLVMGlobalArrayToSkip(&G)) 0
2732 continue; 0
2733 ----
2734 if (isSpecialLLVMGlobalArrayForStaticInit(&G)) { 0
2735 // Generate a format indicator and a unique module id to be a part of ----
2736 // the sinit and sterm function names. ----
2737 if (FormatIndicatorAndUniqueModId.empty()) { 0
2738 std::string UniqueModuleId = getUniqueModuleId(&M); 0
2739 if (UniqueModuleId != "") 0
2740 // TODO: Use source file full path to generate the unique module id ----
2741 // and add a format indicator as a part of function name in case we ----
2742 // will support more than one format. ----
2743 FormatIndicatorAndUniqueModId = "clang_" + UniqueModuleId.substr(1); 0
2744 else ----
2745 // Use the Pid and current time as the unique module id when we cannot ----
2746 // generate one based on a module's strong external symbols. ----
2747 // FIXME: Adjust the comment accordingly after we use source file full ----
2748 // path instead. ----
2749 FormatIndicatorAndUniqueModId = ----
2750 "clangPidTime_" + llvm::itostr(sys::Process::getProcessId()) + 0
2751 "_" + llvm::itostr(time(nullptr)); 0
2752 } 0
2753 ----
2754 emitSpecialLLVMGlobal(&G); 0
2755 continue; 0
2756 } 0
2757 ----
2758 setCsectAlignment(&G); 0
2759 } ----
2760 ----
2761 for (const auto &F : M) 0
2762 setCsectAlignment(&F); 0
2763 ----
2764 // Construct an aliasing list for each GlobalObject. ----
2765 for (const auto &Alias : M.aliases()) { 0
2766 const GlobalObject *Base = Alias.getAliaseeObject(); 0
2767 if (!Base) 0
2768 report_fatal_error( 0
2769 "alias without a base object is not yet supported on AIX"); ----
2770 GOAliasMap[Base].push_back(&Alias); 0
2771 } ----
2772 ----
2773 return Result; 0
2774 } ----

2861 static unsigned mapToSinitPriority(int P) { 0
2862 if (P < 0 || P > 65535) 0
2863 report_fatal_error("invalid init priority"); 0
2864 ----
2865 if (P <= 20) 0
2866 return P; 0
2867 ----
2868 if (P < 81) 0
2869 return 20 + (P - 20) * 16; 0
2870 ----
2871 if (P <= 1124) 0
2872 return 1004 + (P - 81); 0
2873 ----
2874 if (P < 64512) 0
2875 return 2047 + (P - 1124) * 33878; 0
2876 ----
2877 return 2147482625u + (P - 64512); 0
2878 } ----
2879 ----
2880 static std::string convertToSinitPriority(int Priority) { 0
2881 // This helper function converts clang init priority to values used in sinit ----
2882 // and sterm functions. ----
2883 // ----
2884 // The conversion strategies are: ----
2885 // We map the reserved clang/gnu priority range [0, 100] into the sinit/sterm ----
2886 // reserved priority range [0, 1023] by ----
2887 // - directly mapping the first 21 and the last 20 elements of the ranges ----
2888 // - linear interpolating the intermediate values with a step size of 16. ----
2889 // ----
2890 // We map the non reserved clang/gnu priority range of [101, 65535] into the ----
2891 // sinit/sterm priority range [1024, 2147483648] by: ----
2892 // - directly mapping the first and the last 1024 elements of the ranges ----
2893 // - linear interpolating the intermediate values with a step size of 33878. ----
2894 unsigned int P = mapToSinitPriority(Priority); 0
2895 ----
2896 std::string PrioritySuffix; 0
2897 llvm::raw_string_ostream os(PrioritySuffix); 0
2898 os << llvm::format_hex_no_prefix(P, 8); 0
2899 os.flush(); 0
2900 return PrioritySuffix; 0
2901 } 0

2904 const Constant *List, bool IsCtor) { ----
2905 SmallVector Structors; 0
2906 preprocessXXStructorList(DL, List, Structors); 0
2907 if (Structors.empty()) 0
2908 return; 0
2909 ----
2910 unsigned Index = 0; 0
2911 for (Structor &S : Structors) { 0
2912 if (const ConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast(S.Func)) 0
2913 S.Func = CE->getOperand(0); 0
2914 ----
2915 llvm::GlobalAlias::create( 0
2916 GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage, ----
2917 (IsCtor ? llvm::Twine("__sinit") : llvm::Twine("__sterm")) + 0
2918 llvm::Twine(convertToSinitPriority(S.Priority)) + 0
2919 llvm::Twine("_", FormatIndicatorAndUniqueModId) + 0
2920 llvm::Twine("_", llvm::utostr(Index++)), 0
2921 cast(S.Func)); 0
2922 } ----
2923 } 0
